5020 if (slp_node
5021 && TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (vectype))
5022 != TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (op1)))
5023 {
5024 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5025 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5026 "unusable type for last operand in"
5027 " vector/vector shift/rotate.\n");
5028 return false;
5029 }
5030 if (vec_stmt && !slp_node)
5031 {
5032 op1 = fold_convert (TREE_TYPE (vectype), op1);
5033 op1 = vect_init_vector (stmt, op1,
5034 TREE_TYPE (vectype), NULL);
5035 }
5036 }
5037 }
5038 }
5039 }
5040
5041 /* Supportable by target? */
5042 if (!optab)
5043 {
5044 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5045 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5046 "no optab.\n");
5047 return false;
5048 }
5049 vec_mode = TYPE_MODE (vectype);
5050 icode = (int) optab_handler (optab, vec_mode);
5051 if (icode == CODE_FOR_nothing)
5052 {
5053 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5054 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5055 "op not supported by target.\n");
5056 /* Check only during analysis. */
5057 if (GET_MODE_SIZE (vec_mode) != UNITS_PER_WORD
5058 || (vf < vect_min_worthwhile_factor (code)
5059 && !vec_stmt))
5060 return false;
5061 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5062 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
5063 "proceeding using word mode.\n");
5064 }
5065
5066 /* Worthwhile without SIMD support? Check only during analysis. */
5067 if (!VECTOR_MODE_P (TYPE_MODE (vectype))
5068 && vf < vect_min_worthwhile_factor (code)
5069 && !vec_stmt)
5070 {
5071 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5072 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5073 "not worthwhile without SIMD support.\n");
5074 return false;
5075 }
5076
5077 if (!vec_stmt) /* transformation not required. */
5078 {
5079 STMT_VINFO_TYPE (stmt_info) = shift_vec_info_type;
5080 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5081 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
5082 "=== vectorizable_shift ===\n");
5083 vect_model_simple_cost (stmt_info, ncopies, dt, NULL, NULL);
5084 return true;
5085 }
5086
5087 /** Transform. **/
5088
5089 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5090 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
5091 "transform binary/unary operation.\n");
5092
5093 /* Handle def. */
5094 vec_dest = vect_create_destination_var (scalar_dest, vectype);
5095
5096 prev_stmt_info = NULL;
5097 for (j = 0; j < ncopies; j++)
5098 {
5099 /* Handle uses. */
5100 if (j == 0)
5101 {
5102 if (scalar_shift_arg)
5103 {
5104 /* Vector shl and shr insn patterns can be defined with scalar
5105 operand 2 (shift operand). In this case, use constant or loop
5106 invariant op1 directly, without extending it to vector mode
5107 first. */
5108 optab_op2_mode = insn_data[icode].operand[2].mode;
5109 if (!VECTOR_MODE_P (optab_op2_mode))
5110 {
5111 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5112 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
5113 "operand 1 using scalar mode.\n");
5114 vec_oprnd1 = op1;
5115 vec_oprnds1.create (slp_node ? slp_node->vec_stmts_size : 1);
5116 vec_oprnds1.quick_push (vec_oprnd1);
5117 if (slp_node)
5118 {
5119 /* Store vec_oprnd1 for every vector stmt to be created
5120 for SLP_NODE. We check during the analysis that all
5121 the shift arguments are the same.
5122 TODO: Allow different constants for different vector
5123 stmts generated for an SLP instance. */
5124 for (k = 0; k < slp_node->vec_stmts_size - 1; k++)
5125 vec_oprnds1.quick_push (vec_oprnd1);
5126 }
5127 }
5128 }
5129
5130 /* vec_oprnd1 is available if operand 1 should be of a scalar-type
5131 (a special case for certain kind of vector shifts); otherwise,
5132 operand 1 should be of a vector type (the usual case). */
5133 if (vec_oprnd1)
5134 vect_get_vec_defs (op0, NULL_TREE, stmt, &vec_oprnds0, NULL,
5135 slp_node, -1);
5136 else
5137 vect_get_vec_defs (op0, op1, stmt, &vec_oprnds0, &vec_oprnds1,
5138 slp_node, -1);
5139 }
5140 else
5141 vect_get_vec_defs_for_stmt_copy (dt, &vec_oprnds0, &vec_oprnds1);
5142
5143 /* Arguments are ready. Create the new vector stmt. */
5144 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (vec_oprnds0, i, vop0)
5145 {
5146 vop1 = vec_oprnds1[i];
5147 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (vec_dest, code, vop0, vop1);
5148 new_temp = make_ssa_name (vec_dest, new_stmt);
5149 gimple_assign_set_lhs (new_stmt, new_temp);
5150 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
5151 if (slp_node)
5152 SLP_TREE_VEC_STMTS (slp_node).quick_push (new_stmt);
5153 }
5154
5155 if (slp_node)
5156 continue;
5157
5158 if (j == 0)
5159 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info) = *vec_stmt = new_stmt;
5160 else
5161 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (prev_stmt_info) = new_stmt;
5162 prev_stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (new_stmt);
5163 }
5164
5165 vec_oprnds0.release ();
5166 vec_oprnds1.release ();
5167
5168 return true;
5169}
5170
5171
5172/* Function vectorizable_operation.
5173
5174 Check if STMT performs a binary, unary or ternary operation that can
5175 be vectorized.
5176 If VEC_STMT is also passed, vectorize the STMT: create a vectorized
5177 stmt to replace it, put it in VEC_STMT, and insert it at BSI.
5178 Return FALSE if not a vectorizable STMT, TRUE otherwise. */
5179
5180static bool
5181vectorizable_operation (gimple *stmt, gimple_stmt_iterator *gsi,
5182 gimple **vec_stmt, slp_tree slp_node)
5183{
5184 tree vec_dest;
5185 tree scalar_dest;
5186 tree op0, op1 = NULL_TREE, op2 = NULL_TREE;
5187 stmt_vec_info stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (stmt);
5188 tree vectype;
5189 loop_vec_info loop_vinfo = STMT_VINFO_LOOP_VINFO (stmt_info);
5190 enum tree_code code;
5191 machine_mode vec_mode;
5192 tree new_temp;
5193 int op_type;
5194 optab optab;
5195 bool target_support_p;
5196 gimple *def_stmt;
5197 enum vect_def_type dt[3]
5198 = {vect_unknown_def_type, vect_unknown_def_type, vect_unknown_def_type};
5199 gimple *new_stmt = NULL;
5200 stmt_vec_info prev_stmt_info;
5201 int nunits_in;
5202 int nunits_out;
5203 tree vectype_out;
5204 int ncopies;
5205 int j, i;
5206 vec<tree> vec_oprnds0 = vNULL;
5207 vec<tree> vec_oprnds1 = vNULL;
5208 vec<tree> vec_oprnds2 = vNULL;
5209 tree vop0, vop1, vop2;
5210 bb_vec_info bb_vinfo = STMT_VINFO_BB_VINFO (stmt_info);
5211 vec_info *vinfo = stmt_info->vinfo;
5212 int vf;
5213
5214 if (!STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT_P (stmt_info) && !bb_vinfo)
5215 return false;
5216
5217 if (STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (stmt_info) != vect_internal_def
5218 && ! vec_stmt)
5219 return false;
5220
5221 /* Is STMT a vectorizable binary/unary operation? */
5222 if (!is_gimple_assign (stmt))
5223 return false;
5224
5225 if (TREE_CODE (gimple_assign_lhs (stmt)) != SSA_NAME)
5226 return false;
5227
5228 code = gimple_assign_rhs_code (stmt);
5229
5230 /* For pointer addition, we should use the normal plus for
5231 the vector addition. */
5232 if (code == POINTER_PLUS_EXPR)
5233 code = PLUS_EXPR;
5234
5235 /* Support only unary or binary operations. */
5236 op_type = TREE_CODE_LENGTH (code);
5237 if (op_type != unary_op && op_type != binary_op && op_type != ternary_op)
5238 {
5239 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5240 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5241 "num. args = %d (not unary/binary/ternary op).\n",
5242 op_type);
5243 return false;
5244 }
5245
5246 scalar_dest = gimple_assign_lhs (stmt);
5247 vectype_out = STMT_VINFO_VECTYPE (stmt_info);
5248
5249 /* Most operations cannot handle bit-precision types without extra
5250 truncations. */
5251 if (!VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (vectype_out)
5252 && (TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (scalar_dest))
5253 != GET_MODE_PRECISION (TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (scalar_dest))))
5254 /* Exception are bitwise binary operations. */
5255 && code != BIT_IOR_EXPR
5256 && code != BIT_XOR_EXPR
5257 && code != BIT_AND_EXPR)
5258 {
5259 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5260 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5261 "bit-precision arithmetic not supported.\n");
5262 return false;
5263 }
5264
5265 op0 = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
5266 if (!vect_is_simple_use (op0, vinfo, &def_stmt, &dt[0], &vectype))
5267 {
5268 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5269 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5270 "use not simple.\n");
5271 return false;
5272 }
5273 /* If op0 is an external or constant def use a vector type with
5274 the same size as the output vector type. */
5275 if (!vectype)
5276 {
5277 /* For boolean type we cannot determine vectype by
5278 invariant value (don't know whether it is a vector
5279 of booleans or vector of integers). We use output
5280 vectype because operations on boolean don't change
5281 type. */
5282 if (VECT_SCALAR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (op0)))
5283 {
5284 if (!VECT_SCALAR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (scalar_dest)))
5285 {
5286 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5287 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5288 "not supported operation on bool value.\n");
5289 return false;
5290 }
5291 vectype = vectype_out;
5292 }
5293 else
5294 vectype = get_same_sized_vectype (TREE_TYPE (op0), vectype_out);
5295 }
5296 if (vec_stmt)
5297 gcc_assert (vectype);
5298 if (!vectype)
5299 {
5300 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5301 {
5302 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5303 "no vectype for scalar type ");
5304 dump_generic_expr (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, TDF_SLIM,
5305 TREE_TYPE (op0));
5306 dump_printf (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, "\n");
5307 }
5308
5309 return false;
5310 }
5311
5312 nunits_out = TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype_out);
5313 nunits_in = TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype);
5314 if (nunits_out != nunits_in)
5315 return false;
5316
5317 if (op_type == binary_op || op_type == ternary_op)
5318 {
5319 op1 = gimple_assign_rhs2 (stmt);
5320 if (!vect_is_simple_use (op1, vinfo, &def_stmt, &dt[1]))
5321 {
5322 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5323 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5324 "use not simple.\n");
5325 return false;
5326 }
5327 }
5328 if (op_type == ternary_op)
5329 {
5330 op2 = gimple_assign_rhs3 (stmt);
5331 if (!vect_is_simple_use (op2, vinfo, &def_stmt, &dt[2]))
5332 {
5333 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5334 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5335 "use not simple.\n");
5336 return false;
5337 }
5338 }
5339
5340 if (loop_vinfo)
5341 vf = LOOP_VINFO_VECT_FACTOR (loop_vinfo);
5342 else
5343 vf = 1;
5344
5345 /* Multiple types in SLP are handled by creating the appropriate number of
5346 vectorized stmts for each SLP node. Hence, NCOPIES is always 1 in
5347 case of SLP. */
5348 if (slp_node)
5349 ncopies = 1;
5350 else
5351 ncopies = LOOP_VINFO_VECT_FACTOR (loop_vinfo) / nunits_in;
5352
5353 gcc_assert (ncopies >= 1);
5354
5355 /* Shifts are handled in vectorizable_shift (). */
5356 if (code == LSHIFT_EXPR || code == RSHIFT_EXPR || code == LROTATE_EXPR
5357 || code == RROTATE_EXPR)
5358 return false;
5359
5360 /* Supportable by target? */
5361
5362 vec_mode = TYPE_MODE (vectype);
5363 if (code == MULT_HIGHPART_EXPR)
5364 target_support_p = can_mult_highpart_p (vec_mode, TYPE_UNSIGNED (vectype));
5365 else
5366 {
5367 optab = optab_for_tree_code (code, vectype, optab_default);
5368 if (!optab)
5369 {
5370 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5371 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5372 "no optab.\n");
5373 return false;
5374 }
5375 target_support_p = (optab_handler (optab, vec_mode)
5376 != CODE_FOR_nothing);
5377 }
5378
5379 if (!target_support_p)
5380 {
5381 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5382 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5383 "op not supported by target.\n");
5384 /* Check only during analysis. */
5385 if (GET_MODE_SIZE (vec_mode) != UNITS_PER_WORD
5386 || (!vec_stmt && vf < vect_min_worthwhile_factor (code)))
5387 return false;
5388 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5389 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
5390 "proceeding using word mode.\n");
5391 }
5392
5393 /* Worthwhile without SIMD support? Check only during analysis. */
5394 if (!VECTOR_MODE_P (vec_mode)
5395 && !vec_stmt
5396 && vf < vect_min_worthwhile_factor (code))
5397 {
5398 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5399 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5400 "not worthwhile without SIMD support.\n");
5401 return false;
5402 }
5403
5404 if (!vec_stmt) /* transformation not required. */
5405 {
5406 STMT_VINFO_TYPE (stmt_info) = op_vec_info_type;
5407 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5408 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
5409 "=== vectorizable_operation ===\n");
5410 vect_model_simple_cost (stmt_info, ncopies, dt, NULL, NULL);
5411 return true;
5412 }
5413
5414 /** Transform. **/
5415
5416 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5417 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
5418 "transform binary/unary operation.\n");
5419
5420 /* Handle def. */
5421 vec_dest = vect_create_destination_var (scalar_dest, vectype);
5422
5423 /* In case the vectorization factor (VF) is bigger than the number
5424 of elements that we can fit in a vectype (nunits), we have to generate
5425 more than one vector stmt - i.e - we need to "unroll" the
5426 vector stmt by a factor VF/nunits. In doing so, we record a pointer
5427 from one copy of the vector stmt to the next, in the field
5428 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT. This is necessary in order to allow following
5429 stages to find the correct vector defs to be used when vectorizing
5430 stmts that use the defs of the current stmt. The example below
5431 illustrates the vectorization process when VF=16 and nunits=4 (i.e.,
5432 we need to create 4 vectorized stmts):
5433
5434 before vectorization:
5435 RELATED_STMT VEC_STMT
5436 S1: x = memref - -
5437 S2: z = x + 1 - -
5438
5439 step 1: vectorize stmt S1 (done in vectorizable_load. See more details
5440 there):
5441 RELATED_STMT VEC_STMT
5442 VS1_0: vx0 = memref0 VS1_1 -
5443 VS1_1: vx1 = memref1 VS1_2 -
5444 VS1_2: vx2 = memref2 VS1_3 -
5445 VS1_3: vx3 = memref3 - -
5446 S1: x = load - VS1_0
5447 S2: z = x + 1 - -
5448
5449 step2: vectorize stmt S2 (done here):
5450 To vectorize stmt S2 we first need to find the relevant vector
5451 def for the first operand 'x'. This is, as usual, obtained from
5452 the vector stmt recorded in the STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT of the stmt
5453 that defines 'x' (S1). This way we find the stmt VS1_0, and the
5454 relevant vector def 'vx0'. Having found 'vx0' we can generate
5455 the vector stmt VS2_0, and as usual, record it in the
5456 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT of stmt S2.
5457 When creating the second copy (VS2_1), we obtain the relevant vector
5458 def from the vector stmt recorded in the STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT of
5459 stmt VS1_0. This way we find the stmt VS1_1 and the relevant
5460 vector def 'vx1'. Using 'vx1' we create stmt VS2_1 and record a
5461 pointer to it in the STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT of the vector stmt VS2_0.
5462 Similarly when creating stmts VS2_2 and VS2_3. This is the resulting
5463 chain of stmts and pointers:
5464 RELATED_STMT VEC_STMT
5465 VS1_0: vx0 = memref0 VS1_1 -
5466 VS1_1: vx1 = memref1 VS1_2 -
5467 VS1_2: vx2 = memref2 VS1_3 -
5468 VS1_3: vx3 = memref3 - -
5469 S1: x = load - VS1_0
5470 VS2_0: vz0 = vx0 + v1 VS2_1 -
5471 VS2_1: vz1 = vx1 + v1 VS2_2 -
5472 VS2_2: vz2 = vx2 + v1 VS2_3 -
5473 VS2_3: vz3 = vx3 + v1 - -
5474 S2: z = x + 1 - VS2_0 */
5475
5476 prev_stmt_info = NULL;
5477 for (j = 0; j < ncopies; j++)
5478 {
5479 /* Handle uses. */
5480 if (j == 0)
5481 {
5482 if (op_type == binary_op)
5483 vect_get_vec_defs (op0, op1, stmt, &vec_oprnds0, &vec_oprnds1,
5484 slp_node, -1);
5485 else if (op_type == ternary_op)
5486 {
5487 if (slp_node)
5488 {
5489 auto_vec<tree> ops(3);
5490 ops.quick_push (op0);
5491 ops.quick_push (op1);
5492 ops.quick_push (op2);
5493 auto_vec<vec<tree> > vec_defs(3);
5494 vect_get_slp_defs (ops, slp_node, &vec_defs, -1);
5495 vec_oprnds0 = vec_defs[0];
5496 vec_oprnds1 = vec_defs[1];
5497 vec_oprnds2 = vec_defs[2];
5498 }
5499 else
5500 {
5501 vect_get_vec_defs (op0, op1, stmt, &vec_oprnds0, &vec_oprnds1,
5502 NULL, -1);
5503 vect_get_vec_defs (op2, NULL_TREE, stmt, &vec_oprnds2, NULL,
5504 NULL, -1);
5505 }
5506 }
5507 else
5508 vect_get_vec_defs (op0, NULL_TREE, stmt, &vec_oprnds0, NULL,
5509 slp_node, -1);
5510 }
5511 else
5512 {
5513 vect_get_vec_defs_for_stmt_copy (dt, &vec_oprnds0, &vec_oprnds1);
5514 if (op_type == ternary_op)
5515 {
5516 tree vec_oprnd = vec_oprnds2.pop ();
5517 vec_oprnds2.quick_push (vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (dt[2],
5518 vec_oprnd));
5519 }
5520 }
5521
5522 /* Arguments are ready. Create the new vector stmt. */
5523 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (vec_oprnds0, i, vop0)
5524 {
5525 vop1 = ((op_type == binary_op || op_type == ternary_op)
5526 ? vec_oprnds1[i] : NULL_TREE);
5527 vop2 = ((op_type == ternary_op)
5528 ? vec_oprnds2[i] : NULL_TREE);
5529 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (vec_dest, code, vop0, vop1, vop2);
5530 new_temp = make_ssa_name (vec_dest, new_stmt);
5531 gimple_assign_set_lhs (new_stmt, new_temp);
5532 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
5533 if (slp_node)
5534 SLP_TREE_VEC_STMTS (slp_node).quick_push (new_stmt);
5535 }
5536
5537 if (slp_node)
5538 continue;
5539
5540 if (j == 0)
5541 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info) = *vec_stmt = new_stmt;
5542 else
5543 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (prev_stmt_info) = new_stmt;
5544 prev_stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (new_stmt);
5545 }
5546
5547 vec_oprnds0.release ();
5548 vec_oprnds1.release ();
5549 vec_oprnds2.release ();
5550
5551 return true;
5552}
5553
5554/* A helper function to ensure data reference DR's base alignment
5555 for STMT_INFO. */
5556
5557static void
5558ensure_base_align (stmt_vec_info stmt_info, struct data_reference *dr)
5559{
5560 if (!dr->aux)
5561 return;
5562
5563 if (DR_VECT_AUX (dr)->base_misaligned)
5564 {
5565 tree vectype = STMT_VINFO_VECTYPE (stmt_info);
5566 tree base_decl = DR_VECT_AUX (dr)->base_decl;
5567
5568 if (decl_in_symtab_p (base_decl))
5569 symtab_node::get (base_decl)->increase_alignment (TYPE_ALIGN (vectype));
5570 else
5571 {
5572 SET_DECL_ALIGN (base_decl, TYPE_ALIGN (vectype));
5573 DECL_USER_ALIGN (base_decl) = 1;
5574 }
5575 DR_VECT_AUX (dr)->base_misaligned = false;
5576 }
5577}
5578
5579
5580/* Function get_group_alias_ptr_type.
5581
5582 Return the alias type for the group starting at FIRST_STMT. */
5583
5584static tree
5585get_group_alias_ptr_type (gimple *first_stmt)
5586{
5587 struct data_reference *first_dr, *next_dr;
5588 gimple *next_stmt;
5589
5590 first_dr = STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt));
5591 next_stmt = GROUP_NEXT_ELEMENT (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt));
5592 while (next_stmt)
5593 {
5594 next_dr = STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (vinfo_for_stmt (next_stmt));
5595 if (get_alias_set (DR_REF (first_dr))
5596 != get_alias_set (DR_REF (next_dr)))
5597 {
5598 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5599 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
5600 "conflicting alias set types.\n");
5601 return ptr_type_node;
5602 }
5603 next_stmt = GROUP_NEXT_ELEMENT (vinfo_for_stmt (next_stmt));
5604 }
5605 return reference_alias_ptr_type (DR_REF (first_dr));
5606}
5607
5608
5609/* Function vectorizable_store.
5610
5611 Check if STMT defines a non scalar data-ref (array/pointer/structure) that
5612 can be vectorized.
5613 If VEC_STMT is also passed, vectorize the STMT: create a vectorized
5614 stmt to replace it, put it in VEC_STMT, and insert it at BSI.
5615 Return FALSE if not a vectorizable STMT, TRUE otherwise. */
5616
5617static bool
5618vectorizable_store (gimple *stmt, gimple_stmt_iterator *gsi, gimple **vec_stmt,
5619 slp_tree slp_node)
5620{
5621 tree scalar_dest;
5622 tree data_ref;
5623 tree op;
5624 tree vec_oprnd = NULL_TREE;
5625 stmt_vec_info stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (stmt);
5626 struct data_reference *dr = STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (stmt_info), *first_dr = NULL;
5627 tree elem_type;
5628 loop_vec_info loop_vinfo = STMT_VINFO_LOOP_VINFO (stmt_info);
5629 struct loop *loop = NULL;
5630 machine_mode vec_mode;
5631 tree dummy;
5632 enum dr_alignment_support alignment_support_scheme;
5633 gimple *def_stmt;
5634 enum vect_def_type dt;
5635 stmt_vec_info prev_stmt_info = NULL;
5636 tree dataref_ptr = NULL_TREE;
5637 tree dataref_offset = NULL_TREE;
5638 gimple *ptr_incr = NULL;
5639 int ncopies;
5640 int j;
5641 gimple *next_stmt, *first_stmt;
5642 bool grouped_store;
5643 unsigned int group_size, i;
5644 vec<tree> oprnds = vNULL;
5645 vec<tree> result_chain = vNULL;
5646 bool inv_p;
5647 tree offset = NULL_TREE;
5648 vec<tree> vec_oprnds = vNULL;
5649 bool slp = (slp_node != NULL);
5650 unsigned int vec_num;
5651 bb_vec_info bb_vinfo = STMT_VINFO_BB_VINFO (stmt_info);
5652 vec_info *vinfo = stmt_info->vinfo;
5653 tree aggr_type;
5654 gather_scatter_info gs_info;
5655 enum vect_def_type scatter_src_dt = vect_unknown_def_type;
5656 gimple *new_stmt;
5657 int vf;
5658 vec_load_store_type vls_type;
5659 tree ref_type;
5660
5661 if (!STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT_P (stmt_info) && !bb_vinfo)
5662 return false;
5663
5664 if (STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (stmt_info) != vect_internal_def
5665 && ! vec_stmt)
5666 return false;
5667
5668 /* Is vectorizable store? */
5669
5670 if (!is_gimple_assign (stmt))
5671 return false;
5672
5673 scalar_dest = gimple_assign_lhs (stmt);
5674 if (TREE_CODE (scalar_dest) == VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR
5675 && is_pattern_stmt_p (stmt_info))
5676 scalar_dest = TREE_OPERAND (scalar_dest, 0);
5677 if (TREE_CODE (scalar_dest) != ARRAY_REF
5678 && TREE_CODE (scalar_dest) != BIT_FIELD_REF
5679 && TREE_CODE (scalar_dest) != INDIRECT_REF
5680 && TREE_CODE (scalar_dest) != COMPONENT_REF
5681 && TREE_CODE (scalar_dest) != IMAGPART_EXPR
5682 && TREE_CODE (scalar_dest) != REALPART_EXPR
5683 && TREE_CODE (scalar_dest) != MEM_REF)
5684 return false;
5685
5686 /* Cannot have hybrid store SLP -- that would mean storing to the
5687 same location twice. */
5688 gcc_assert (slp == PURE_SLP_STMT (stmt_info));
5689
5690 gcc_assert (gimple_assign_single_p (stmt));
5691
5692 tree vectype = STMT_VINFO_VECTYPE (stmt_info), rhs_vectype = NULL_TREE;
5693 unsigned int nunits = TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype);
5694
5695 if (loop_vinfo)
5696 {
5697 loop = LOOP_VINFO_LOOP (loop_vinfo);
5698 vf = LOOP_VINFO_VECT_FACTOR (loop_vinfo);
5699 }
5700 else
5701 vf = 1;
5702
5703 /* Multiple types in SLP are handled by creating the appropriate number of
5704 vectorized stmts for each SLP node. Hence, NCOPIES is always 1 in
5705 case of SLP. */
5706 if (slp)
5707 ncopies = 1;
5708 else
5709 ncopies = LOOP_VINFO_VECT_FACTOR (loop_vinfo) / nunits;
5710
5711 gcc_assert (ncopies >= 1);
5712
5713 /* FORNOW. This restriction should be relaxed. */
5714 if (loop && nested_in_vect_loop_p (loop, stmt) && ncopies > 1)
5715 {
5716 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5717 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5718 "multiple types in nested loop.\n");
5719 return false;
5720 }
5721
5722 op = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
5723
5724 /* In the case this is a store from a STRING_CST make sure
5725 native_encode_expr can handle it. */
5726 if (TREE_CODE (op) == STRING_CST
5727 && ! can_native_encode_string_p (op))
5728 return false;
5729
5730 if (!vect_is_simple_use (op, vinfo, &def_stmt, &dt, &rhs_vectype))
5731 {
5732 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5733 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
5734 "use not simple.\n");
5735 return false;
5736 }
5737
5738 if (dt == vect_constant_def || dt == vect_external_def)
5739 vls_type = VLS_STORE_INVARIANT;
5740 else
5741 vls_type = VLS_STORE;
5742
5743 if (rhs_vectype && !useless_type_conversion_p (vectype, rhs_vectype))
5744 return false;
5745
5746 elem_type = TREE_TYPE (vectype);
5747 vec_mode = TYPE_MODE (vectype);
5748
5749 /* FORNOW. In some cases can vectorize even if data-type not supported
5750 (e.g. - array initialization with 0). */
5751 if (optab_handler (mov_optab, vec_mode) == CODE_FOR_nothing)
5752 return false;
5753
5754 if (!STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (stmt_info))
5755 return false;
5756
5757 vect_memory_access_type memory_access_type;
5758 if (!get_load_store_type (stmt, vectype, slp, vls_type, ncopies,
5759 &memory_access_type, &gs_info))
5760 return false;
5761
5762 if (!vec_stmt) /* transformation not required. */
5763 {
5764 STMT_VINFO_MEMORY_ACCESS_TYPE (stmt_info) = memory_access_type;
5765 STMT_VINFO_TYPE (stmt_info) = store_vec_info_type;
5766 /* The SLP costs are calculated during SLP analysis. */
5767 if (!PURE_SLP_STMT (stmt_info))
5768 vect_model_store_cost (stmt_info, ncopies, memory_access_type, dt,
5769 NULL, NULL, NULL);
5770 return true;
5771 }
5772 gcc_assert (memory_access_type == STMT_VINFO_MEMORY_ACCESS_TYPE (stmt_info));
5773
5774 /** Transform. **/
5775
5776 ensure_base_align (stmt_info, dr);
5777
5778 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_GATHER_SCATTER)
5779 {
5780 tree vec_oprnd0 = NULL_TREE, vec_oprnd1 = NULL_TREE, op, src;
5781 tree arglist = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (gs_info.decl));
5782 tree rettype, srctype, ptrtype, idxtype, masktype, scaletype;
5783 tree ptr, mask, var, scale, perm_mask = NULL_TREE;
5784 edge pe = loop_preheader_edge (loop);
5785 gimple_seq seq;
5786 basic_block new_bb;
5787 enum { NARROW, NONE, WIDEN } modifier;
5788 int scatter_off_nunits = TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (gs_info.offset_vectype);
5789
5790 if (nunits == (unsigned int) scatter_off_nunits)
5791 modifier = NONE;
5792 else if (nunits == (unsigned int) scatter_off_nunits / 2)
5793 {
5794 unsigned char *sel = XALLOCAVEC (unsigned char, scatter_off_nunits);
5795 modifier = WIDEN;
5796
5797 for (i = 0; i < (unsigned int) scatter_off_nunits; ++i)
5798 sel[i] = i | nunits;
5799
5800 perm_mask = vect_gen_perm_mask_checked (gs_info.offset_vectype, sel);
5801 gcc_assert (perm_mask != NULL_TREE);
5802 }
5803 else if (nunits == (unsigned int) scatter_off_nunits * 2)
5804 {
5805 unsigned char *sel = XALLOCAVEC (unsigned char, nunits);
5806 modifier = NARROW;
5807
5808 for (i = 0; i < (unsigned int) nunits; ++i)
5809 sel[i] = i | scatter_off_nunits;
5810
5811 perm_mask = vect_gen_perm_mask_checked (vectype, sel);
5812 gcc_assert (perm_mask != NULL_TREE);
5813 ncopies *= 2;
5814 }
5815 else
5816 gcc_unreachable ();
5817
5818 rettype = TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (gs_info.decl));
5819 ptrtype = TREE_VALUE (arglist); arglist = TREE_CHAIN (arglist);
5820 masktype = TREE_VALUE (arglist); arglist = TREE_CHAIN (arglist);
5821 idxtype = TREE_VALUE (arglist); arglist = TREE_CHAIN (arglist);
5822 srctype = TREE_VALUE (arglist); arglist = TREE_CHAIN (arglist);
5823 scaletype = TREE_VALUE (arglist);
5824
5825 gcc_checking_assert (TREE_CODE (masktype) == INTEGER_TYPE
5826 && TREE_CODE (rettype) == VOID_TYPE);
5827
5828 ptr = fold_convert (ptrtype, gs_info.base);
5829 if (!is_gimple_min_invariant (ptr))
5830 {
5831 ptr = force_gimple_operand (ptr, &seq, true, NULL_TREE);
5832 new_bb = gsi_insert_seq_on_edge_immediate (pe, seq);
5833 gcc_assert (!new_bb);
5834 }
5835
5836 /* Currently we support only unconditional scatter stores,
5837 so mask should be all ones. */
5838 mask = build_int_cst (masktype, -1);
5839 mask = vect_init_vector (stmt, mask, masktype, NULL);
5840
5841 scale = build_int_cst (scaletype, gs_info.scale);
5842
5843 prev_stmt_info = NULL;
5844 for (j = 0; j < ncopies; ++j)
5845 {
5846 if (j == 0)
5847 {
5848 src = vec_oprnd1
5849 = vect_get_vec_def_for_operand (gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt), stmt);
5850 op = vec_oprnd0
5851 = vect_get_vec_def_for_operand (gs_info.offset, stmt);
5852 }
5853 else if (modifier != NONE && (j & 1))
5854 {
5855 if (modifier == WIDEN)
5856 {
5857 src = vec_oprnd1
5858 = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (scatter_src_dt, vec_oprnd1);
5859 op = permute_vec_elements (vec_oprnd0, vec_oprnd0, perm_mask,
5860 stmt, gsi);
5861 }
5862 else if (modifier == NARROW)
5863 {
5864 src = permute_vec_elements (vec_oprnd1, vec_oprnd1, perm_mask,
5865 stmt, gsi);
5866 op = vec_oprnd0
5867 = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (gs_info.offset_dt,
5868 vec_oprnd0);
5869 }
5870 else
5871 gcc_unreachable ();
5872 }
5873 else
5874 {
5875 src = vec_oprnd1
5876 = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (scatter_src_dt, vec_oprnd1);
5877 op = vec_oprnd0
5878 = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (gs_info.offset_dt,
5879 vec_oprnd0);
5880 }
5881
5882 if (!useless_type_conversion_p (srctype, TREE_TYPE (src)))
5883 {
5884 gcc_assert (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (TREE_TYPE (src))
5885 == TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (srctype));
5886 var = vect_get_new_ssa_name (srctype, vect_simple_var);
5887 src = build1 (VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR, srctype, src);
5888 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (var, VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR, src);
5889 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
5890 src = var;
5891 }
5892
5893 if (!useless_type_conversion_p (idxtype, TREE_TYPE (op)))
5894 {
5895 gcc_assert (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (TREE_TYPE (op))
5896 == TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (idxtype));
5897 var = vect_get_new_ssa_name (idxtype, vect_simple_var);
5898 op = build1 (VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR, idxtype, op);
5899 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (var, VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR, op);
5900 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
5901 op = var;
5902 }
5903
5904 new_stmt
5905 = gimple_build_call (gs_info.decl, 5, ptr, mask, op, src, scale);
5906
5907 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
5908
5909 if (prev_stmt_info == NULL)
5910 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info) = *vec_stmt = new_stmt;
5911 else
5912 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (prev_stmt_info) = new_stmt;
5913 prev_stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (new_stmt);
5914 }
5915 return true;
5916 }
5917
5918 grouped_store = STMT_VINFO_GROUPED_ACCESS (stmt_info);
5919 if (grouped_store)
5920 {
5921 first_stmt = GROUP_FIRST_ELEMENT (stmt_info);
5922 first_dr = STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt));
5923 group_size = GROUP_SIZE (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt));
5924
5925 GROUP_STORE_COUNT (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt))++;
5926
5927 /* FORNOW */
5928 gcc_assert (!loop || !nested_in_vect_loop_p (loop, stmt));
5929
5930 /* We vectorize all the stmts of the interleaving group when we
5931 reach the last stmt in the group. */
5932 if (GROUP_STORE_COUNT (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt))
5933 < GROUP_SIZE (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt))
5934 && !slp)
5935 {
5936 *vec_stmt = NULL;
5937 return true;
5938 }
5939
5940 if (slp)
5941 {
5942 grouped_store = false;
5943 /* VEC_NUM is the number of vect stmts to be created for this
5944 group. */
5945 vec_num = SLP_TREE_NUMBER_OF_VEC_STMTS (slp_node);
5946 first_stmt = SLP_TREE_SCALAR_STMTS (slp_node)[0];
5947 gcc_assert (GROUP_FIRST_ELEMENT (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt)) == first_stmt);
5948 first_dr = STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt));
5949 op = gimple_assign_rhs1 (first_stmt);
5950 }
5951 else
5952 /* VEC_NUM is the number of vect stmts to be created for this
5953 group. */
5954 vec_num = group_size;
5955
5956 ref_type = get_group_alias_ptr_type (first_stmt);
5957 }
5958 else
5959 {
5960 first_stmt = stmt;
5961 first_dr = dr;
5962 group_size = vec_num = 1;
5963 ref_type = reference_alias_ptr_type (DR_REF (first_dr));
5964 }
5965
5966 if (dump_enabled_p ())
5967 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
5968 "transform store. ncopies = %d\n", ncopies);
5969
5970 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_ELEMENTWISE
5971 || memory_access_type == VMAT_STRIDED_SLP)
5972 {
5973 gimple_stmt_iterator incr_gsi;
5974 bool insert_after;
5975 gimple *incr;
5976 tree offvar;
5977 tree ivstep;
5978 tree running_off;
5979 gimple_seq stmts = NULL;
5980 tree stride_base, stride_step, alias_off;
5981 tree vec_oprnd;
5982 unsigned int g;
5983
5984 gcc_assert (!nested_in_vect_loop_p (loop, stmt));
5985
5986 stride_base
5987 = fold_build_pointer_plus
5988 (unshare_expr (DR_BASE_ADDRESS (first_dr)),
5989 size_binop (PLUS_EXPR,
5990 convert_to_ptrofftype (unshare_expr (DR_OFFSET (first_dr))),
5991 convert_to_ptrofftype (DR_INIT (first_dr))));
5992 stride_step = fold_convert (sizetype, unshare_expr (DR_STEP (first_dr)));
5993
5994 /* For a store with loop-invariant (but other than power-of-2)
5995 stride (i.e. not a grouped access) like so:
5996
5997 for (i = 0; i < n; i += stride)
5998 array[i] = ...;
5999
6000 we generate a new induction variable and new stores from
6001 the components of the (vectorized) rhs:
6002
6003 for (j = 0; ; j += VF*stride)
6004 vectemp = ...;
6005 tmp1 = vectemp[0];
6006 array[j] = tmp1;
6007 tmp2 = vectemp[1];
6008 array[j + stride] = tmp2;
6009 ...
6010 */
6011
6012 unsigned nstores = nunits;
6013 unsigned lnel = 1;
6014 tree ltype = elem_type;
6015 if (slp)
6016 {
6017 if (group_size < nunits
6018 && nunits % group_size == 0)
6019 {
6020 nstores = nunits / group_size;
6021 lnel = group_size;
6022 ltype = build_vector_type (elem_type, group_size);
6023 }
6024 else if (group_size >= nunits
6025 && group_size % nunits == 0)
6026 {
6027 nstores = 1;
6028 lnel = nunits;
6029 ltype = vectype;
6030 }
6031 ltype = build_aligned_type (ltype, TYPE_ALIGN (elem_type));
6032 ncopies = SLP_TREE_NUMBER_OF_VEC_STMTS (slp_node);
6033 }
6034
6035 ivstep = stride_step;
6036 ivstep = fold_build2 (MULT_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (ivstep), ivstep,
6037 build_int_cst (TREE_TYPE (ivstep), vf));
6038
6039 standard_iv_increment_position (loop, &incr_gsi, &insert_after);
6040
6041 create_iv (stride_base, ivstep, NULL,
6042 loop, &incr_gsi, insert_after,
6043 &offvar, NULL);
6044 incr = gsi_stmt (incr_gsi);
6045 set_vinfo_for_stmt (incr, new_stmt_vec_info (incr, loop_vinfo));
6046
6047 stride_step = force_gimple_operand (stride_step, &stmts, true, NULL_TREE);
6048 if (stmts)
6049 gsi_insert_seq_on_edge_immediate (loop_preheader_edge (loop), stmts);
6050
6051 prev_stmt_info = NULL;
6052 alias_off = build_int_cst (ref_type, 0);
6053 next_stmt = first_stmt;
6054 for (g = 0; g < group_size; g++)
6055 {
6056 running_off = offvar;
6057 if (g)
6058 {
6059 tree size = TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (ltype);
6060 tree pos = fold_build2 (MULT_EXPR, sizetype, size_int (g),
6061 size);
6062 tree newoff = copy_ssa_name (running_off, NULL);
6063 incr = gimple_build_assign (newoff, POINTER_PLUS_EXPR,
6064 running_off, pos);
6065 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, incr, gsi);
6066 running_off = newoff;
6067 }
6068 unsigned int group_el = 0;
6069 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT
6070 elsz = tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (TREE_TYPE (vectype)));
6071 for (j = 0; j < ncopies; j++)
6072 {
6073 /* We've set op and dt above, from gimple_assign_rhs1(stmt),
6074 and first_stmt == stmt. */
6075 if (j == 0)
6076 {
6077 if (slp)
6078 {
6079 vect_get_vec_defs (op, NULL_TREE, stmt, &vec_oprnds, NULL,
6080 slp_node, -1);
6081 vec_oprnd = vec_oprnds[0];
6082 }
6083 else
6084 {
6085 gcc_assert (gimple_assign_single_p (next_stmt));
6086 op = gimple_assign_rhs1 (next_stmt);
6087 vec_oprnd = vect_get_vec_def_for_operand (op, next_stmt);
6088 }
6089 }
6090 else
6091 {
6092 if (slp)
6093 vec_oprnd = vec_oprnds[j];
6094 else
6095 {
6096 vect_is_simple_use (vec_oprnd, vinfo, &def_stmt, &dt);
6097 vec_oprnd = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (dt, vec_oprnd);
6098 }
6099 }
6100
6101 for (i = 0; i < nstores; i++)
6102 {
6103 tree newref, newoff;
6104 gimple *incr, *assign;
6105 tree size = TYPE_SIZE (ltype);
6106 /* Extract the i'th component. */
6107 tree pos = fold_build2 (MULT_EXPR, bitsizetype,
6108 bitsize_int (i), size);
6109 tree elem = fold_build3 (BIT_FIELD_REF, ltype, vec_oprnd,
6110 size, pos);
6111
6112 elem = force_gimple_operand_gsi (gsi, elem, true,
6113 NULL_TREE, true,
6114 GSI_SAME_STMT);
6115
6116 tree this_off = build_int_cst (TREE_TYPE (alias_off),
6117 group_el * elsz);
6118 newref = build2 (MEM_REF, ltype,
6119 running_off, this_off);
6120
6121 /* And store it to *running_off. */
6122 assign = gimple_build_assign (newref, elem);
6123 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, assign, gsi);
6124
6125 group_el += lnel;
6126 if (! slp
6127 || group_el == group_size)
6128 {
6129 newoff = copy_ssa_name (running_off, NULL);
6130 incr = gimple_build_assign (newoff, POINTER_PLUS_EXPR,
6131 running_off, stride_step);
6132 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, incr, gsi);
6133
6134 running_off = newoff;
6135 group_el = 0;
6136 }
6137 if (g == group_size - 1
6138 && !slp)
6139 {
6140 if (j == 0 && i == 0)
6141 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info)
6142 = *vec_stmt = assign;
6143 else
6144 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (prev_stmt_info) = assign;
6145 prev_stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (assign);
6146 }
6147 }
6148 }
6149 next_stmt = GROUP_NEXT_ELEMENT (vinfo_for_stmt (next_stmt));
6150 if (slp)
6151 break;
6152 }
6153
6154 vec_oprnds.release ();
6155 return true;
6156 }
6157
6158 auto_vec<tree> dr_chain (group_size);
6159 oprnds.create (group_size);
6160
6161 alignment_support_scheme = vect_supportable_dr_alignment (first_dr, false);
6162 gcc_assert (alignment_support_scheme);
6163 /* Targets with store-lane instructions must not require explicit
6164 realignment. */
6165 gcc_assert (memory_access_type != VMAT_LOAD_STORE_LANES
6166 || alignment_support_scheme == dr_aligned
6167 || alignment_support_scheme == dr_unaligned_supported);
6168
6169 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_CONTIGUOUS_DOWN
6170 || memory_access_type == VMAT_CONTIGUOUS_REVERSE)
6171 offset = size_int (-TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype) + 1);
6172
6173 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_LOAD_STORE_LANES)
6174 aggr_type = build_array_type_nelts (elem_type, vec_num * nunits);
6175 else
6176 aggr_type = vectype;
6177
6178 /* In case the vectorization factor (VF) is bigger than the number
6179 of elements that we can fit in a vectype (nunits), we have to generate
6180 more than one vector stmt - i.e - we need to "unroll" the
6181 vector stmt by a factor VF/nunits. For more details see documentation in
6182 vect_get_vec_def_for_copy_stmt. */
6183
6184 /* In case of interleaving (non-unit grouped access):
6185
6186 S1: &base + 2 = x2
6187 S2: &base = x0
6188 S3: &base + 1 = x1
6189 S4: &base + 3 = x3
6190
6191 We create vectorized stores starting from base address (the access of the
6192 first stmt in the chain (S2 in the above example), when the last store stmt
6193 of the chain (S4) is reached:
6194
6195 VS1: &base = vx2
6196 VS2: &base + vec_size*1 = vx0
6197 VS3: &base + vec_size*2 = vx1
6198 VS4: &base + vec_size*3 = vx3
6199
6200 Then permutation statements are generated:
6201
6202 VS5: vx5 = VEC_PERM_EXPR < vx0, vx3, {0, 8, 1, 9, 2, 10, 3, 11} >
6203 VS6: vx6 = VEC_PERM_EXPR < vx0, vx3, {4, 12, 5, 13, 6, 14, 7, 15} >
6204 ...
6205
6206 And they are put in STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT of the corresponding scalar stmts
6207 (the order of the data-refs in the output of vect_permute_store_chain
6208 corresponds to the order of scalar stmts in the interleaving chain - see
6209 the documentation of vect_permute_store_chain()).
6210
6211 In case of both multiple types and interleaving, above vector stores and
6212 permutation stmts are created for every copy. The result vector stmts are
6213 put in STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT for the first copy and in the corresponding
6214 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT for the next copies.
6215 */
6216
6217 prev_stmt_info = NULL;
6218 for (j = 0; j < ncopies; j++)
6219 {
6220
6221 if (j == 0)
6222 {
6223 if (slp)
6224 {
6225 /* Get vectorized arguments for SLP_NODE. */
6226 vect_get_vec_defs (op, NULL_TREE, stmt, &vec_oprnds,
6227 NULL, slp_node, -1);
6228
6229 vec_oprnd = vec_oprnds[0];
6230 }
6231 else
6232 {
6233 /* For interleaved stores we collect vectorized defs for all the
6234 stores in the group in DR_CHAIN and OPRNDS. DR_CHAIN is then
6235 used as an input to vect_permute_store_chain(), and OPRNDS as
6236 an input to vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy() for the next copy.
6237
6238 If the store is not grouped, GROUP_SIZE is 1, and DR_CHAIN and
6239 OPRNDS are of size 1. */
6240 next_stmt = first_stmt;
6241 for (i = 0; i < group_size; i++)
6242 {
6243 /* Since gaps are not supported for interleaved stores,
6244 GROUP_SIZE is the exact number of stmts in the chain.
6245 Therefore, NEXT_STMT can't be NULL_TREE. In case that
6246 there is no interleaving, GROUP_SIZE is 1, and only one
6247 iteration of the loop will be executed. */
6248 gcc_assert (next_stmt
6249 && gimple_assign_single_p (next_stmt));
6250 op = gimple_assign_rhs1 (next_stmt);
6251
6252 vec_oprnd = vect_get_vec_def_for_operand (op, next_stmt);
6253 dr_chain.quick_push (vec_oprnd);
6254 oprnds.quick_push (vec_oprnd);
6255 next_stmt = GROUP_NEXT_ELEMENT (vinfo_for_stmt (next_stmt));
6256 }
6257 }
6258
6259 /* We should have catched mismatched types earlier. */
6260 gcc_assert (useless_type_conversion_p (vectype,
6261 TREE_TYPE (vec_oprnd)));
6262 bool simd_lane_access_p
6263 = STMT_VINFO_SIMD_LANE_ACCESS_P (stmt_info);
6264 if (simd_lane_access_p
6265 && TREE_CODE (DR_BASE_ADDRESS (first_dr)) == ADDR_EXPR
6266 && VAR_P (TREE_OPERAND (DR_BASE_ADDRESS (first_dr), 0))
6267 && integer_zerop (DR_OFFSET (first_dr))
6268 && integer_zerop (DR_INIT (first_dr))
6269 && alias_sets_conflict_p (get_alias_set (aggr_type),
6270 get_alias_set (TREE_TYPE (ref_type))))
6271 {
6272 dataref_ptr = unshare_expr (DR_BASE_ADDRESS (first_dr));
6273 dataref_offset = build_int_cst (ref_type, 0);
6274 inv_p = false;
6275 }
6276 else
6277 dataref_ptr
6278 = vect_create_data_ref_ptr (first_stmt, aggr_type,
6279 simd_lane_access_p ? loop : NULL,
6280 offset, &dummy, gsi, &ptr_incr,
6281 simd_lane_access_p, &inv_p);
6282 gcc_assert (bb_vinfo || !inv_p);
6283 }
6284 else
6285 {
6286 /* For interleaved stores we created vectorized defs for all the
6287 defs stored in OPRNDS in the previous iteration (previous copy).
6288 DR_CHAIN is then used as an input to vect_permute_store_chain(),
6289 and OPRNDS as an input to vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy() for the
6290 next copy.
6291 If the store is not grouped, GROUP_SIZE is 1, and DR_CHAIN and
6292 OPRNDS are of size 1. */
6293 for (i = 0; i < group_size; i++)
6294 {
6295 op = oprnds[i];
6296 vect_is_simple_use (op, vinfo, &def_stmt, &dt);
6297 vec_oprnd = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (dt, op);
6298 dr_chain[i] = vec_oprnd;
6299 oprnds[i] = vec_oprnd;
6300 }
6301 if (dataref_offset)
6302 dataref_offset
6303 = int_const_binop (PLUS_EXPR, dataref_offset,
6304 TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (aggr_type));
6305 else
6306 dataref_ptr = bump_vector_ptr (dataref_ptr, ptr_incr, gsi, stmt,
6307 TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (aggr_type));
6308 }
6309
6310 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_LOAD_STORE_LANES)
6311 {
6312 tree vec_array;
6313
6314 /* Combine all the vectors into an array. */
6315 vec_array = create_vector_array (vectype, vec_num);
6316 for (i = 0; i < vec_num; i++)
6317 {
6318 vec_oprnd = dr_chain[i];
6319 write_vector_array (stmt, gsi, vec_oprnd, vec_array, i);
6320 }
6321
6322 /* Emit:
6323 MEM_REF[...all elements...] = STORE_LANES (VEC_ARRAY). */
6324 data_ref = create_array_ref (aggr_type, dataref_ptr, ref_type);
6325 new_stmt = gimple_build_call_internal (IFN_STORE_LANES, 1, vec_array);
6326 gimple_call_set_lhs (new_stmt, data_ref);
6327 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
6328 }
6329 else
6330 {
6331 new_stmt = NULL;
6332 if (grouped_store)
6333 {
6334 if (j == 0)
6335 result_chain.create (group_size);
6336 /* Permute. */
6337 vect_permute_store_chain (dr_chain, group_size, stmt, gsi,
6338 &result_chain);
6339 }
6340
6341 next_stmt = first_stmt;
6342 for (i = 0; i < vec_num; i++)
6343 {
6344 unsigned align, misalign;
6345
6346 if (i > 0)
6347 /* Bump the vector pointer. */
6348 dataref_ptr = bump_vector_ptr (dataref_ptr, ptr_incr, gsi,
6349 stmt, NULL_TREE);
6350
6351 if (slp)
6352 vec_oprnd = vec_oprnds[i];
6353 else if (grouped_store)
6354 /* For grouped stores vectorized defs are interleaved in
6355 vect_permute_store_chain(). */
6356 vec_oprnd = result_chain[i];
6357
6358 data_ref = fold_build2 (MEM_REF, vectype,
6359 dataref_ptr,
6360 dataref_offset
6361 ? dataref_offset
6362 : build_int_cst (ref_type, 0));
6363 align = TYPE_ALIGN_UNIT (vectype);
6364 if (aligned_access_p (first_dr))
6365 misalign = 0;
6366 else if (DR_MISALIGNMENT (first_dr) == -1)
6367 {
6368 if (DR_VECT_AUX (first_dr)->base_element_aligned)
6369 align = TYPE_ALIGN_UNIT (elem_type);
6370 else
6371 align = get_object_alignment (DR_REF (first_dr))
6372 / BITS_PER_UNIT;
6373 misalign = 0;
6374 TREE_TYPE (data_ref)
6375 = build_aligned_type (TREE_TYPE (data_ref),
6376 align * BITS_PER_UNIT);
6377 }
6378 else
6379 {
6380 TREE_TYPE (data_ref)
6381 = build_aligned_type (TREE_TYPE (data_ref),
6382 TYPE_ALIGN (elem_type));
6383 misalign = DR_MISALIGNMENT (first_dr);
6384 }
6385 if (dataref_offset == NULL_TREE
6386 && TREE_CODE (dataref_ptr) == SSA_NAME)
6387 set_ptr_info_alignment (get_ptr_info (dataref_ptr), align,
6388 misalign);
6389
6390 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_CONTIGUOUS_REVERSE)
6391 {
6392 tree perm_mask = perm_mask_for_reverse (vectype);
6393 tree perm_dest
6394 = vect_create_destination_var (gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt),
6395 vectype);
6396 tree new_temp = make_ssa_name (perm_dest);
6397
6398 /* Generate the permute statement. */
6399 gimple *perm_stmt
6400 = gimple_build_assign (new_temp, VEC_PERM_EXPR, vec_oprnd,
6401 vec_oprnd, perm_mask);
6402 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, perm_stmt, gsi);
6403
6404 perm_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (new_temp);
6405 vec_oprnd = new_temp;
6406 }
6407
6408 /* Arguments are ready. Create the new vector stmt. */
6409 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (data_ref, vec_oprnd);
6410 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
6411
6412 if (slp)
6413 continue;
6414
6415 next_stmt = GROUP_NEXT_ELEMENT (vinfo_for_stmt (next_stmt));
6416 if (!next_stmt)
6417 break;
6418 }
6419 }
6420 if (!slp)
6421 {
6422 if (j == 0)
6423 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info) = *vec_stmt = new_stmt;
6424 else
6425 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (prev_stmt_info) = new_stmt;
6426 prev_stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (new_stmt);
6427 }
6428 }
6429
6430 oprnds.release ();
6431 result_chain.release ();
6432 vec_oprnds.release ();
6433
6434 return true;
6435}
6436
6437/* Given a vector type VECTYPE, turns permutation SEL into the equivalent
6438 VECTOR_CST mask. No checks are made that the target platform supports the
6439 mask, so callers may wish to test can_vec_perm_p separately, or use
6440 vect_gen_perm_mask_checked. */
6441
6442tree
6443vect_gen_perm_mask_any (tree vectype, const unsigned char *sel)
6444{
6445 tree mask_elt_type, mask_type, mask_vec, *mask_elts;
6446 int i, nunits;
6447
6448 nunits = TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype);
6449
6450 mask_elt_type = lang_hooks.types.type_for_mode
6451 (int_mode_for_mode (TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (vectype))), 1);
6452 mask_type = get_vectype_for_scalar_type (mask_elt_type);
6453
6454 mask_elts = XALLOCAVEC (tree, nunits);
6455 for (i = nunits - 1; i >= 0; i--)
6456 mask_elts[i] = build_int_cst (mask_elt_type, sel[i]);
6457 mask_vec = build_vector (mask_type, mask_elts);
6458
6459 return mask_vec;
6460}
6461
6462/* Checked version of vect_gen_perm_mask_any. Asserts can_vec_perm_p,
6463 i.e. that the target supports the pattern _for arbitrary input vectors_. */
6464
6465tree
6466vect_gen_perm_mask_checked (tree vectype, const unsigned char *sel)
6467{
6468 gcc_assert (can_vec_perm_p (TYPE_MODE (vectype), false, sel));
6469 return vect_gen_perm_mask_any (vectype, sel);
6470}
6471
6472/* Given a vector variable X and Y, that was generated for the scalar
6473 STMT, generate instructions to permute the vector elements of X and Y
6474 using permutation mask MASK_VEC, insert them at *GSI and return the
6475 permuted vector variable. */
6476
6477static tree
6478permute_vec_elements (tree x, tree y, tree mask_vec, gimple *stmt,
6479 gimple_stmt_iterator *gsi)
6480{
6481 tree vectype = TREE_TYPE (x);
6482 tree perm_dest, data_ref;
6483 gimple *perm_stmt;
6484
6485 perm_dest = vect_create_destination_var (gimple_get_lhs (stmt), vectype);
6486 data_ref = make_ssa_name (perm_dest);
6487
6488 /* Generate the permute statement. */
6489 perm_stmt = gimple_build_assign (data_ref, VEC_PERM_EXPR, x, y, mask_vec);
6490 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, perm_stmt, gsi);
6491
6492 return data_ref;
6493}
6494
6495/* Hoist the definitions of all SSA uses on STMT out of the loop LOOP,
6496 inserting them on the loops preheader edge. Returns true if we
6497 were successful in doing so (and thus STMT can be moved then),
6498 otherwise returns false. */
6499
6500static bool
6501hoist_defs_of_uses (gimple *stmt, struct loop *loop)
6502{
6503 ssa_op_iter i;
6504 tree op;
6505 bool any = false;
6506
6507 FOR_EACH_SSA_TREE_OPERAND (op, stmt, i, SSA_OP_USE)
6508 {
6509 gimple *def_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (op);
6510 if (!gimple_nop_p (def_stmt)
6511 && flow_bb_inside_loop_p (loop, gimple_bb (def_stmt)))
6512 {
6513 /* Make sure we don't need to recurse. While we could do
6514 so in simple cases when there are more complex use webs
6515 we don't have an easy way to preserve stmt order to fulfil
6516 dependencies within them. */
6517 tree op2;
6518 ssa_op_iter i2;
6519 if (gimple_code (def_stmt) == GIMPLE_PHI)
6520 return false;
6521 FOR_EACH_SSA_TREE_OPERAND (op2, def_stmt, i2, SSA_OP_USE)
6522 {
6523 gimple *def_stmt2 = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (op2);
6524 if (!gimple_nop_p (def_stmt2)
6525 && flow_bb_inside_loop_p (loop, gimple_bb (def_stmt2)))
6526 return false;
6527 }
6528 any = true;
6529 }
6530 }
6531
6532 if (!any)
6533 return true;
6534
6535 FOR_EACH_SSA_TREE_OPERAND (op, stmt, i, SSA_OP_USE)
6536 {
6537 gimple *def_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (op);
6538 if (!gimple_nop_p (def_stmt)
6539 && flow_bb_inside_loop_p (loop, gimple_bb (def_stmt)))
6540 {
6541 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi = gsi_for_stmt (def_stmt);
6542 gsi_remove (&gsi, false);
6543 gsi_insert_on_edge_immediate (loop_preheader_edge (loop), def_stmt);
6544 }
6545 }
6546
6547 return true;
6548}
6549
6550/* vectorizable_load.
6551
6552 Check if STMT reads a non scalar data-ref (array/pointer/structure) that
6553 can be vectorized.
6554 If VEC_STMT is also passed, vectorize the STMT: create a vectorized
6555 stmt to replace it, put it in VEC_STMT, and insert it at BSI.
6556 Return FALSE if not a vectorizable STMT, TRUE otherwise. */
6557
6558static bool
6559vectorizable_load (gimple *stmt, gimple_stmt_iterator *gsi, gimple **vec_stmt,
6560 slp_tree slp_node, slp_instance slp_node_instance)
6561{
6562 tree scalar_dest;
6563 tree vec_dest = NULL;
6564 tree data_ref = NULL;
6565 stmt_vec_info stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (stmt);
6566 stmt_vec_info prev_stmt_info;
6567 loop_vec_info loop_vinfo = STMT_VINFO_LOOP_VINFO (stmt_info);
6568 struct loop *loop = NULL;
6569 struct loop *containing_loop = (gimple_bb (stmt))->loop_father;
6570 bool nested_in_vect_loop = false;
6571 struct data_reference *dr = STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (stmt_info), *first_dr = NULL;
6572 tree elem_type;
6573 tree new_temp;
6574 machine_mode mode;
6575 gimple *new_stmt = NULL;
6576 tree dummy;
6577 enum dr_alignment_support alignment_support_scheme;
6578 tree dataref_ptr = NULL_TREE;
6579 tree dataref_offset = NULL_TREE;
6580 gimple *ptr_incr = NULL;
6581 int ncopies;
6582 int i, j, group_size, group_gap_adj;
6583 tree msq = NULL_TREE, lsq;
6584 tree offset = NULL_TREE;
6585 tree byte_offset = NULL_TREE;
6586 tree realignment_token = NULL_TREE;
6587 gphi *phi = NULL;
6588 vec<tree> dr_chain = vNULL;
6589 bool grouped_load = false;
6590 gimple *first_stmt;
6591 gimple *first_stmt_for_drptr = NULL;
6592 bool inv_p;
6593 bool compute_in_loop = false;
6594 struct loop *at_loop;
6595 int vec_num;
6596 bool slp = (slp_node != NULL);
6597 bool slp_perm = false;
6598 enum tree_code code;
6599 bb_vec_info bb_vinfo = STMT_VINFO_BB_VINFO (stmt_info);
6600 int vf;
6601 tree aggr_type;
6602 gather_scatter_info gs_info;
6603 vec_info *vinfo = stmt_info->vinfo;
6604 tree ref_type;
6605
6606 if (!STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT_P (stmt_info) && !bb_vinfo)
6607 return false;
6608
6609 if (STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (stmt_info) != vect_internal_def
6610 && ! vec_stmt)
6611 return false;
6612
6613 /* Is vectorizable load? */
6614 if (!is_gimple_assign (stmt))
6615 return false;
6616
6617 scalar_dest = gimple_assign_lhs (stmt);
6618 if (TREE_CODE (scalar_dest) != SSA_NAME)
6619 return false;
6620
6621 code = gimple_assign_rhs_code (stmt);
6622 if (code != ARRAY_REF
6623 && code != BIT_FIELD_REF
6624 && code != INDIRECT_REF
6625 && code != COMPONENT_REF
6626 && code != IMAGPART_EXPR
6627 && code != REALPART_EXPR
6628 && code != MEM_REF
6629 && TREE_CODE_CLASS (code) != tcc_declaration)
6630 return false;
6631
6632 if (!STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (stmt_info))
6633 return false;
6634
6635 tree vectype = STMT_VINFO_VECTYPE (stmt_info);
6636 int nunits = TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype);
6637
6638 if (loop_vinfo)
6639 {
6640 loop = LOOP_VINFO_LOOP (loop_vinfo);
6641 nested_in_vect_loop = nested_in_vect_loop_p (loop, stmt);
6642 vf = LOOP_VINFO_VECT_FACTOR (loop_vinfo);
6643 }
6644 else
6645 vf = 1;
6646
6647 /* Multiple types in SLP are handled by creating the appropriate number of
6648 vectorized stmts for each SLP node. Hence, NCOPIES is always 1 in
6649 case of SLP. */
6650 if (slp)
6651 ncopies = 1;
6652 else
6653 ncopies = LOOP_VINFO_VECT_FACTOR (loop_vinfo) / nunits;
6654
6655 gcc_assert (ncopies >= 1);
6656
6657 /* FORNOW. This restriction should be relaxed. */
6658 if (nested_in_vect_loop && ncopies > 1)
6659 {
6660 if (dump_enabled_p ())
6661 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
6662 "multiple types in nested loop.\n");
6663 return false;
6664 }
6665
6666 /* Invalidate assumptions made by dependence analysis when vectorization
6667 on the unrolled body effectively re-orders stmts. */
6668 if (ncopies > 1
6669 && STMT_VINFO_MIN_NEG_DIST (stmt_info) != 0
6670 && ((unsigned)LOOP_VINFO_VECT_FACTOR (loop_vinfo)
6671 > STMT_VINFO_MIN_NEG_DIST (stmt_info)))
6672 {
6673 if (dump_enabled_p ())
6674 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
6675 "cannot perform implicit CSE when unrolling "
6676 "with negative dependence distance\n");
6677 return false;
6678 }
6679
6680 elem_type = TREE_TYPE (vectype);
6681 mode = TYPE_MODE (vectype);
6682
6683 /* FORNOW. In some cases can vectorize even if data-type not supported
6684 (e.g. - data copies). */
6685 if (optab_handler (mov_optab, mode) == CODE_FOR_nothing)
6686 {
6687 if (dump_enabled_p ())
6688 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
6689 "Aligned load, but unsupported type.\n");
6690 return false;
6691 }
6692
6693 /* Check if the load is a part of an interleaving chain. */
6694 if (STMT_VINFO_GROUPED_ACCESS (stmt_info))
6695 {
6696 grouped_load = true;
6697 /* FORNOW */
6698 gcc_assert (!nested_in_vect_loop);
6699 gcc_assert (!STMT_VINFO_GATHER_SCATTER_P (stmt_info));
6700
6701 first_stmt = GROUP_FIRST_ELEMENT (stmt_info);
6702 group_size = GROUP_SIZE (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt));
6703
6704 if (slp && SLP_TREE_LOAD_PERMUTATION (slp_node).exists ())
6705 slp_perm = true;
6706
6707 /* Invalidate assumptions made by dependence analysis when vectorization
6708 on the unrolled body effectively re-orders stmts. */
6709 if (!PURE_SLP_STMT (stmt_info)
6710 && STMT_VINFO_MIN_NEG_DIST (stmt_info) != 0
6711 && ((unsigned)LOOP_VINFO_VECT_FACTOR (loop_vinfo)
6712 > STMT_VINFO_MIN_NEG_DIST (stmt_info)))
6713 {
6714 if (dump_enabled_p ())
6715 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
6716 "cannot perform implicit CSE when performing "
6717 "group loads with negative dependence distance\n");
6718 return false;
6719 }
6720
6721 /* Similarly when the stmt is a load that is both part of a SLP
6722 instance and a loop vectorized stmt via the same-dr mechanism
6723 we have to give up. */
6724 if (STMT_VINFO_GROUP_SAME_DR_STMT (stmt_info)
6725 && (STMT_SLP_TYPE (stmt_info)
6726 != STMT_SLP_TYPE (vinfo_for_stmt
6727 (STMT_VINFO_GROUP_SAME_DR_STMT (stmt_info)))))
6728 {
6729 if (dump_enabled_p ())
6730 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
6731 "conflicting SLP types for CSEd load\n");
6732 return false;
6733 }
6734 }
6735
6736 vect_memory_access_type memory_access_type;
6737 if (!get_load_store_type (stmt, vectype, slp, VLS_LOAD, ncopies,
6738 &memory_access_type, &gs_info))
6739 return false;
6740
6741 if (!vec_stmt) /* transformation not required. */
6742 {
6743 if (!slp)
6744 STMT_VINFO_MEMORY_ACCESS_TYPE (stmt_info) = memory_access_type;
6745 STMT_VINFO_TYPE (stmt_info) = load_vec_info_type;
6746 /* The SLP costs are calculated during SLP analysis. */
6747 if (!PURE_SLP_STMT (stmt_info))
6748 vect_model_load_cost (stmt_info, ncopies, memory_access_type,
6749 NULL, NULL, NULL);
6750 return true;
6751 }
6752
6753 if (!slp)
6754 gcc_assert (memory_access_type
6755 == STMT_VINFO_MEMORY_ACCESS_TYPE (stmt_info));
6756
6757 if (dump_enabled_p ())
6758 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
6759 "transform load. ncopies = %d\n", ncopies);
6760
6761 /** Transform. **/
6762
6763 ensure_base_align (stmt_info, dr);
6764
6765 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_GATHER_SCATTER)
6766 {
6767 tree vec_oprnd0 = NULL_TREE, op;
6768 tree arglist = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (gs_info.decl));
6769 tree rettype, srctype, ptrtype, idxtype, masktype, scaletype;
6770 tree ptr, mask, var, scale, merge, perm_mask = NULL_TREE, prev_res = NULL_TREE;
6771 edge pe = loop_preheader_edge (loop);
6772 gimple_seq seq;
6773 basic_block new_bb;
6774 enum { NARROW, NONE, WIDEN } modifier;
6775 int gather_off_nunits = TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (gs_info.offset_vectype);
6776
6777 if (nunits == gather_off_nunits)
6778 modifier = NONE;
6779 else if (nunits == gather_off_nunits / 2)
6780 {
6781 unsigned char *sel = XALLOCAVEC (unsigned char, gather_off_nunits);
6782 modifier = WIDEN;
6783
6784 for (i = 0; i < gather_off_nunits; ++i)
6785 sel[i] = i | nunits;
6786
6787 perm_mask = vect_gen_perm_mask_checked (gs_info.offset_vectype, sel);
6788 }
6789 else if (nunits == gather_off_nunits * 2)
6790 {
6791 unsigned char *sel = XALLOCAVEC (unsigned char, nunits);
6792 modifier = NARROW;
6793
6794 for (i = 0; i < nunits; ++i)
6795 sel[i] = i < gather_off_nunits
6796 ? i : i + nunits - gather_off_nunits;
6797
6798 perm_mask = vect_gen_perm_mask_checked (vectype, sel);
6799 ncopies *= 2;
6800 }
6801 else
6802 gcc_unreachable ();
6803
6804 rettype = TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (gs_info.decl));
6805 srctype = TREE_VALUE (arglist); arglist = TREE_CHAIN (arglist);
6806 ptrtype = TREE_VALUE (arglist); arglist = TREE_CHAIN (arglist);
6807 idxtype = TREE_VALUE (arglist); arglist = TREE_CHAIN (arglist);
6808 masktype = TREE_VALUE (arglist); arglist = TREE_CHAIN (arglist);
6809 scaletype = TREE_VALUE (arglist);
6810 gcc_checking_assert (types_compatible_p (srctype, rettype));
6811
6812 vec_dest = vect_create_destination_var (scalar_dest, vectype);
6813
6814 ptr = fold_convert (ptrtype, gs_info.base);
6815 if (!is_gimple_min_invariant (ptr))
6816 {
6817 ptr = force_gimple_operand (ptr, &seq, true, NULL_TREE);
6818 new_bb = gsi_insert_seq_on_edge_immediate (pe, seq);
6819 gcc_assert (!new_bb);
6820 }
6821
6822 /* Currently we support only unconditional gather loads,
6823 so mask should be all ones. */
6824 if (TREE_CODE (masktype) == INTEGER_TYPE)
6825 mask = build_int_cst (masktype, -1);
6826 else if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (masktype)) == INTEGER_TYPE)
6827 {
6828 mask = build_int_cst (TREE_TYPE (masktype), -1);
6829 mask = build_vector_from_val (masktype, mask);
6830 mask = vect_init_vector (stmt, mask, masktype, NULL);
6831 }
6832 else if (SCALAR_FLOAT_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (masktype)))
6833 {
6834 REAL_VALUE_TYPE r;
6835 long tmp[6];
6836 for (j = 0; j < 6; ++j)
6837 tmp[j] = -1;
6838 real_from_target (&r, tmp, TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (masktype)));
6839 mask = build_real (TREE_TYPE (masktype), r);
6840 mask = build_vector_from_val (masktype, mask);
6841 mask = vect_init_vector (stmt, mask, masktype, NULL);
6842 }
6843 else
6844 gcc_unreachable ();
6845
6846 scale = build_int_cst (scaletype, gs_info.scale);
6847
6848 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (rettype)) == INTEGER_TYPE)
6849 merge = build_int_cst (TREE_TYPE (rettype), 0);
6850 else if (SCALAR_FLOAT_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (rettype)))
6851 {
6852 REAL_VALUE_TYPE r;
6853 long tmp[6];
6854 for (j = 0; j < 6; ++j)
6855 tmp[j] = 0;
6856 real_from_target (&r, tmp, TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (rettype)));
6857 merge = build_real (TREE_TYPE (rettype), r);
6858 }
6859 else
6860 gcc_unreachable ();
6861 merge = build_vector_from_val (rettype, merge);
6862 merge = vect_init_vector (stmt, merge, rettype, NULL);
6863
6864 prev_stmt_info = NULL;
6865 for (j = 0; j < ncopies; ++j)
6866 {
6867 if (modifier == WIDEN && (j & 1))
6868 op = permute_vec_elements (vec_oprnd0, vec_oprnd0,
6869 perm_mask, stmt, gsi);
6870 else if (j == 0)
6871 op = vec_oprnd0
6872 = vect_get_vec_def_for_operand (gs_info.offset, stmt);
6873 else
6874 op = vec_oprnd0
6875 = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (gs_info.offset_dt, vec_oprnd0);
6876
6877 if (!useless_type_conversion_p (idxtype, TREE_TYPE (op)))
6878 {
6879 gcc_assert (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (TREE_TYPE (op))
6880 == TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (idxtype));
6881 var = vect_get_new_ssa_name (idxtype, vect_simple_var);
6882 op = build1 (VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR, idxtype, op);
6883 new_stmt
6884 = gimple_build_assign (var, VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR, op);
6885 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
6886 op = var;
6887 }
6888
6889 new_stmt
6890 = gimple_build_call (gs_info.decl, 5, merge, ptr, op, mask, scale);
6891
6892 if (!useless_type_conversion_p (vectype, rettype))
6893 {
6894 gcc_assert (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype)
6895 == TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (rettype));
6896 op = vect_get_new_ssa_name (rettype, vect_simple_var);
6897 gimple_call_set_lhs (new_stmt, op);
6898 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
6899 var = make_ssa_name (vec_dest);
6900 op = build1 (VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR, vectype, op);
6901 new_stmt
6902 = gimple_build_assign (var, VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR, op);
6903 }
6904 else
6905 {
6906 var = make_ssa_name (vec_dest, new_stmt);
6907 gimple_call_set_lhs (new_stmt, var);
6908 }
6909
6910 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
6911
6912 if (modifier == NARROW)
6913 {
6914 if ((j & 1) == 0)
6915 {
6916 prev_res = var;
6917 continue;
6918 }
6919 var = permute_vec_elements (prev_res, var,
6920 perm_mask, stmt, gsi);
6921 new_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (var);
6922 }
6923
6924 if (prev_stmt_info == NULL)
6925 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info) = *vec_stmt = new_stmt;
6926 else
6927 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (prev_stmt_info) = new_stmt;
6928 prev_stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (new_stmt);
6929 }
6930 return true;
6931 }
6932
6933 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_ELEMENTWISE
6934 || memory_access_type == VMAT_STRIDED_SLP)
6935 {
6936 gimple_stmt_iterator incr_gsi;
6937 bool insert_after;
6938 gimple *incr;
6939 tree offvar;
6940 tree ivstep;
6941 tree running_off;
6942 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *v = NULL;
6943 gimple_seq stmts = NULL;
6944 tree stride_base, stride_step, alias_off;
6945
6946 gcc_assert (!nested_in_vect_loop);
6947
6948 if (slp && grouped_load)
6949 {
6950 first_stmt = GROUP_FIRST_ELEMENT (stmt_info);
6951 first_dr = STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt));
6952 group_size = GROUP_SIZE (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt));
6953 ref_type = get_group_alias_ptr_type (first_stmt);
6954 }
6955 else
6956 {
6957 first_stmt = stmt;
6958 first_dr = dr;
6959 group_size = 1;
6960 ref_type = reference_alias_ptr_type (DR_REF (first_dr));
6961 }
6962
6963 stride_base
6964 = fold_build_pointer_plus
6965 (DR_BASE_ADDRESS (first_dr),
6966 size_binop (PLUS_EXPR,
6967 convert_to_ptrofftype (DR_OFFSET (first_dr)),
6968 convert_to_ptrofftype (DR_INIT (first_dr))));
6969 stride_step = fold_convert (sizetype, DR_STEP (first_dr));
6970
6971 /* For a load with loop-invariant (but other than power-of-2)
6972 stride (i.e. not a grouped access) like so:
6973
6974 for (i = 0; i < n; i += stride)
6975 ... = array[i];
6976
6977 we generate a new induction variable and new accesses to
6978 form a new vector (or vectors, depending on ncopies):
6979
6980 for (j = 0; ; j += VF*stride)
6981 tmp1 = array[j];
6982 tmp2 = array[j + stride];
6983 ...
6984 vectemp = {tmp1, tmp2, ...}
6985 */
6986
6987 ivstep = fold_build2 (MULT_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (stride_step), stride_step,
6988 build_int_cst (TREE_TYPE (stride_step), vf));
6989
6990 standard_iv_increment_position (loop, &incr_gsi, &insert_after);
6991
6992 create_iv (unshare_expr (stride_base), unshare_expr (ivstep), NULL,
6993 loop, &incr_gsi, insert_after,
6994 &offvar, NULL);
6995 incr = gsi_stmt (incr_gsi);
6996 set_vinfo_for_stmt (incr, new_stmt_vec_info (incr, loop_vinfo));
6997
6998 stride_step = force_gimple_operand (unshare_expr (stride_step),
6999 &stmts, true, NULL_TREE);
7000 if (stmts)
7001 gsi_insert_seq_on_edge_immediate (loop_preheader_edge (loop), stmts);
7002
7003 prev_stmt_info = NULL;
7004 running_off = offvar;
7005 alias_off = build_int_cst (ref_type, 0);
7006 int nloads = nunits;
7007 int lnel = 1;
7008 tree ltype = TREE_TYPE (vectype);
7009 tree lvectype = vectype;
7010 auto_vec<tree> dr_chain;
7011 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_STRIDED_SLP)
7012 {
7013 if (group_size < nunits)
7014 {
7015 /* Avoid emitting a constructor of vector elements by performing
7016 the loads using an integer type of the same size,
7017 constructing a vector of those and then re-interpreting it
7018 as the original vector type. This works around the fact
7019 that the vec_init optab was only designed for scalar
7020 element modes and thus expansion goes through memory.
7021 This avoids a huge runtime penalty due to the general
7022 inability to perform store forwarding from smaller stores
7023 to a larger load. */
7024 unsigned lsize
7025 = group_size * TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (vectype));
7026 enum machine_mode elmode = mode_for_size (lsize, MODE_INT, 0);
7027 enum machine_mode vmode = mode_for_vector (elmode,
7028 nunits / group_size);
7029 /* If we can't construct such a vector fall back to
7030 element loads of the original vector type. */
7031 if (VECTOR_MODE_P (vmode)
7032 && optab_handler (vec_init_optab, vmode) != CODE_FOR_nothing)
7033 {
7034 nloads = nunits / group_size;
7035 lnel = group_size;
7036 ltype = build_nonstandard_integer_type (lsize, 1);
7037 lvectype = build_vector_type (ltype, nloads);
7038 }
7039 }
7040 else
7041 {
7042 nloads = 1;
7043 lnel = nunits;
7044 ltype = vectype;
7045 }
7046 ltype = build_aligned_type (ltype, TYPE_ALIGN (TREE_TYPE (vectype)));
7047 }
7048 if (slp)
7049 {
7050 /* For SLP permutation support we need to load the whole group,
7051 not only the number of vector stmts the permutation result
7052 fits in. */
7053 if (slp_perm)
7054 {
7055 ncopies = (group_size * vf + nunits - 1) / nunits;
7056 dr_chain.create (ncopies);
7057 }
7058 else
7059 ncopies = SLP_TREE_NUMBER_OF_VEC_STMTS (slp_node);
7060 }
7061 int group_el = 0;
7062 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT
7063 elsz = tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (TREE_TYPE (vectype)));
7064 for (j = 0; j < ncopies; j++)
7065 {
7066 if (nloads > 1)
7067 vec_alloc (v, nloads);
7068 for (i = 0; i < nloads; i++)
7069 {
7070 tree this_off = build_int_cst (TREE_TYPE (alias_off),
7071 group_el * elsz);
7072 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (make_ssa_name (ltype),
7073 build2 (MEM_REF, ltype,
7074 running_off, this_off));
7075 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
7076 if (nloads > 1)
7077 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT (v, NULL_TREE,
7078 gimple_assign_lhs (new_stmt));
7079
7080 group_el += lnel;
7081 if (! slp
7082 || group_el == group_size)
7083 {
7084 tree newoff = copy_ssa_name (running_off);
7085 gimple *incr = gimple_build_assign (newoff, POINTER_PLUS_EXPR,
7086 running_off, stride_step);
7087 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, incr, gsi);
7088
7089 running_off = newoff;
7090 group_el = 0;
7091 }
7092 }
7093 if (nloads > 1)
7094 {
7095 tree vec_inv = build_constructor (lvectype, v);
7096 new_temp = vect_init_vector (stmt, vec_inv, lvectype, gsi);
7097 new_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (new_temp);
7098 if (lvectype != vectype)
7099 {
7100 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (make_ssa_name (vectype),
7101 VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR,
7102 build1 (VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR,
7103 vectype, new_temp));
7104 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
7105 }
7106 }
7107
7108 if (slp)
7109 {
7110 if (slp_perm)
7111 dr_chain.quick_push (gimple_assign_lhs (new_stmt));
7112 else
7113 SLP_TREE_VEC_STMTS (slp_node).quick_push (new_stmt);
7114 }
7115 else
7116 {
7117 if (j == 0)
7118 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info) = *vec_stmt = new_stmt;
7119 else
7120 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (prev_stmt_info) = new_stmt;
7121 prev_stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (new_stmt);
7122 }
7123 }
7124 if (slp_perm)
7125 {
7126 unsigned n_perms;
7127 vect_transform_slp_perm_load (slp_node, dr_chain, gsi, vf,
7128 slp_node_instance, false, &n_perms);
7129 }
7130 return true;
7131 }
7132
7133 if (grouped_load)
7134 {
7135 first_stmt = GROUP_FIRST_ELEMENT (stmt_info);
7136 group_size = GROUP_SIZE (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt));
7137 /* For SLP vectorization we directly vectorize a subchain
7138 without permutation. */
7139 if (slp && ! SLP_TREE_LOAD_PERMUTATION (slp_node).exists ())
7140 first_stmt = SLP_TREE_SCALAR_STMTS (slp_node)[0];
7141 /* For BB vectorization always use the first stmt to base
7142 the data ref pointer on. */
7143 if (bb_vinfo)
7144 first_stmt_for_drptr = SLP_TREE_SCALAR_STMTS (slp_node)[0];
7145
7146 /* Check if the chain of loads is already vectorized. */
7147 if (STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt))
7148 /* For SLP we would need to copy over SLP_TREE_VEC_STMTS.
7149 ??? But we can only do so if there is exactly one
7150 as we have no way to get at the rest. Leave the CSE
7151 opportunity alone.
7152 ??? With the group load eventually participating
7153 in multiple different permutations (having multiple
7154 slp nodes which refer to the same group) the CSE
7155 is even wrong code. See PR56270. */
7156 && !slp)
7157 {
7158 *vec_stmt = STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info);
7159 return true;
7160 }
7161 first_dr = STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt));
7162 group_gap_adj = 0;
7163
7164 /* VEC_NUM is the number of vect stmts to be created for this group. */
7165 if (slp)
7166 {
7167 grouped_load = false;
7168 /* For SLP permutation support we need to load the whole group,
7169 not only the number of vector stmts the permutation result
7170 fits in. */
7171 if (slp_perm)
7172 {
7173 vec_num = (group_size * vf + nunits - 1) / nunits;
7174 group_gap_adj = vf * group_size - nunits * vec_num;
7175 }
7176 else
7177 {
7178 vec_num = SLP_TREE_NUMBER_OF_VEC_STMTS (slp_node);
7179 group_gap_adj
7180 = group_size - SLP_INSTANCE_GROUP_SIZE (slp_node_instance);
7181 }
7182 }
7183 else
7184 vec_num = group_size;
7185
7186 ref_type = get_group_alias_ptr_type (first_stmt);
7187 }
7188 else
7189 {
7190 first_stmt = stmt;
7191 first_dr = dr;
7192 group_size = vec_num = 1;
7193 group_gap_adj = 0;
7194 ref_type = reference_alias_ptr_type (DR_REF (first_dr));
7195 }
7196
7197 alignment_support_scheme = vect_supportable_dr_alignment (first_dr, false);
7198 gcc_assert (alignment_support_scheme);
7199 /* Targets with load-lane instructions must not require explicit
7200 realignment. */
7201 gcc_assert (memory_access_type != VMAT_LOAD_STORE_LANES
7202 || alignment_support_scheme == dr_aligned
7203 || alignment_support_scheme == dr_unaligned_supported);
7204
7205 /* In case the vectorization factor (VF) is bigger than the number
7206 of elements that we can fit in a vectype (nunits), we have to generate
7207 more than one vector stmt - i.e - we need to "unroll" the
7208 vector stmt by a factor VF/nunits. In doing so, we record a pointer
7209 from one copy of the vector stmt to the next, in the field
7210 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT. This is necessary in order to allow following
7211 stages to find the correct vector defs to be used when vectorizing
7212 stmts that use the defs of the current stmt. The example below
7213 illustrates the vectorization process when VF=16 and nunits=4 (i.e., we
7214 need to create 4 vectorized stmts):
7215
7216 before vectorization:
7217 RELATED_STMT VEC_STMT
7218 S1: x = memref - -
7219 S2: z = x + 1 - -
7220
7221 step 1: vectorize stmt S1:
7222 We first create the vector stmt VS1_0, and, as usual, record a
7223 pointer to it in the STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT of the scalar stmt S1.
7224 Next, we create the vector stmt VS1_1, and record a pointer to
7225 it in the STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT of the vector stmt VS1_0.
7226 Similarly, for VS1_2 and VS1_3. This is the resulting chain of
7227 stmts and pointers:
7228 RELATED_STMT VEC_STMT
7229 VS1_0: vx0 = memref0 VS1_1 -
7230 VS1_1: vx1 = memref1 VS1_2 -
7231 VS1_2: vx2 = memref2 VS1_3 -
7232 VS1_3: vx3 = memref3 - -
7233 S1: x = load - VS1_0
7234 S2: z = x + 1 - -
7235
7236 See in documentation in vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy for how the
7237 information we recorded in RELATED_STMT field is used to vectorize
7238 stmt S2. */
7239
7240 /* In case of interleaving (non-unit grouped access):
7241
7242 S1: x2 = &base + 2
7243 S2: x0 = &base
7244 S3: x1 = &base + 1
7245 S4: x3 = &base + 3
7246
7247 Vectorized loads are created in the order of memory accesses
7248 starting from the access of the first stmt of the chain:
7249
7250 VS1: vx0 = &base
7251 VS2: vx1 = &base + vec_size*1
7252 VS3: vx3 = &base + vec_size*2
7253 VS4: vx4 = &base + vec_size*3
7254
7255 Then permutation statements are generated:
7256
7257 VS5: vx5 = VEC_PERM_EXPR < vx0, vx1, { 0, 2, ..., i*2 } >
7258 VS6: vx6 = VEC_PERM_EXPR < vx0, vx1, { 1, 3, ..., i*2+1 } >
7259 ...
7260
7261 And they are put in STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT of the corresponding scalar stmts
7262 (the order of the data-refs in the output of vect_permute_load_chain
7263 corresponds to the order of scalar stmts in the interleaving chain - see
7264 the documentation of vect_permute_load_chain()).
7265 The generation of permutation stmts and recording them in
7266 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT is done in vect_transform_grouped_load().
7267
7268 In case of both multiple types and interleaving, the vector loads and
7269 permutation stmts above are created for every copy. The result vector
7270 stmts are put in STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT for the first copy and in the
7271 corresponding STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT for the next copies. */
7272
7273 /* If the data reference is aligned (dr_aligned) or potentially unaligned
7274 on a target that supports unaligned accesses (dr_unaligned_supported)
7275 we generate the following code:
7276 p = initial_addr;
7277 indx = 0;
7278 loop {
7279 p = p + indx * vectype_size;
7280 vec_dest = *(p);
7281 indx = indx + 1;
7282 }
7283
7284 Otherwise, the data reference is potentially unaligned on a target that
7285 does not support unaligned accesses (dr_explicit_realign_optimized) -
7286 then generate the following code, in which the data in each iteration is
7287 obtained by two vector loads, one from the previous iteration, and one
7288 from the current iteration:
7289 p1 = initial_addr;
7290 msq_init = *(floor(p1))
7291 p2 = initial_addr + VS - 1;
7292 realignment_token = call target_builtin;
7293 indx = 0;
7294 loop {
7295 p2 = p2 + indx * vectype_size
7296 lsq = *(floor(p2))
7297 vec_dest = realign_load (msq, lsq, realignment_token)
7298 indx = indx + 1;
7299 msq = lsq;
7300 } */
7301
7302 /* If the misalignment remains the same throughout the execution of the
7303 loop, we can create the init_addr and permutation mask at the loop
7304 preheader. Otherwise, it needs to be created inside the loop.
7305 This can only occur when vectorizing memory accesses in the inner-loop
7306 nested within an outer-loop that is being vectorized. */
7307
7308 if (nested_in_vect_loop
7309 && (TREE_INT_CST_LOW (DR_STEP (dr))
7310 % GET_MODE_SIZE (TYPE_MODE (vectype)) != 0))
7311 {
7312 gcc_assert (alignment_support_scheme != dr_explicit_realign_optimized);
7313 compute_in_loop = true;
7314 }
7315
7316 if ((alignment_support_scheme == dr_explicit_realign_optimized
7317 || alignment_support_scheme == dr_explicit_realign)
7318 && !compute_in_loop)
7319 {
7320 msq = vect_setup_realignment (first_stmt, gsi, &realignment_token,
7321 alignment_support_scheme, NULL_TREE,
7322 &at_loop);
7323 if (alignment_support_scheme == dr_explicit_realign_optimized)
7324 {
7325 phi = as_a <gphi *> (SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (msq));
7326 byte_offset = size_binop (MINUS_EXPR, TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (vectype),
7327 size_one_node);
7328 }
7329 }
7330 else
7331 at_loop = loop;
7332
7333 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_CONTIGUOUS_REVERSE)
7334 offset = size_int (-TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype) + 1);
7335
7336 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_LOAD_STORE_LANES)
7337 aggr_type = build_array_type_nelts (elem_type, vec_num * nunits);
7338 else
7339 aggr_type = vectype;
7340
7341 prev_stmt_info = NULL;
7342 int group_elt = 0;
7343 for (j = 0; j < ncopies; j++)
7344 {
7345 /* 1. Create the vector or array pointer update chain. */
7346 if (j == 0)
7347 {
7348 bool simd_lane_access_p
7349 = STMT_VINFO_SIMD_LANE_ACCESS_P (stmt_info);
7350 if (simd_lane_access_p
7351 && TREE_CODE (DR_BASE_ADDRESS (first_dr)) == ADDR_EXPR
7352 && VAR_P (TREE_OPERAND (DR_BASE_ADDRESS (first_dr), 0))
7353 && integer_zerop (DR_OFFSET (first_dr))
7354 && integer_zerop (DR_INIT (first_dr))
7355 && alias_sets_conflict_p (get_alias_set (aggr_type),
7356 get_alias_set (TREE_TYPE (ref_type)))
7357 && (alignment_support_scheme == dr_aligned
7358 || alignment_support_scheme == dr_unaligned_supported))
7359 {
7360 dataref_ptr = unshare_expr (DR_BASE_ADDRESS (first_dr));
7361 dataref_offset = build_int_cst (ref_type, 0);
7362 inv_p = false;
7363 }
7364 else if (first_stmt_for_drptr
7365 && first_stmt != first_stmt_for_drptr)
7366 {
7367 dataref_ptr
7368 = vect_create_data_ref_ptr (first_stmt_for_drptr, aggr_type,
7369 at_loop, offset, &dummy, gsi,
7370 &ptr_incr, simd_lane_access_p,
7371 &inv_p, byte_offset);
7372 /* Adjust the pointer by the difference to first_stmt. */
7373 data_reference_p ptrdr
7374 = STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (vinfo_for_stmt (first_stmt_for_drptr));
7375 tree diff = fold_convert (sizetype,
7376 size_binop (MINUS_EXPR,
7377 DR_INIT (first_dr),
7378 DR_INIT (ptrdr)));
7379 dataref_ptr = bump_vector_ptr (dataref_ptr, ptr_incr, gsi,
7380 stmt, diff);
7381 }
7382 else
7383 dataref_ptr
7384 = vect_create_data_ref_ptr (first_stmt, aggr_type, at_loop,
7385 offset, &dummy, gsi, &ptr_incr,
7386 simd_lane_access_p, &inv_p,
7387 byte_offset);
7388 }
7389 else if (dataref_offset)
7390 dataref_offset = int_const_binop (PLUS_EXPR, dataref_offset,
7391 TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (aggr_type));
7392 else
7393 dataref_ptr = bump_vector_ptr (dataref_ptr, ptr_incr, gsi, stmt,
7394 TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (aggr_type));
7395
7396 if (grouped_load || slp_perm)
7397 dr_chain.create (vec_num);
7398
7399 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_LOAD_STORE_LANES)
7400 {
7401 tree vec_array;
7402
7403 vec_array = create_vector_array (vectype, vec_num);
7404
7405 /* Emit:
7406 VEC_ARRAY = LOAD_LANES (MEM_REF[...all elements...]). */
7407 data_ref = create_array_ref (aggr_type, dataref_ptr, ref_type);
7408 new_stmt = gimple_build_call_internal (IFN_LOAD_LANES, 1, data_ref);
7409 gimple_call_set_lhs (new_stmt, vec_array);
7410 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
7411
7412 /* Extract each vector into an SSA_NAME. */
7413 for (i = 0; i < vec_num; i++)
7414 {
7415 new_temp = read_vector_array (stmt, gsi, scalar_dest,
7416 vec_array, i);
7417 dr_chain.quick_push (new_temp);
7418 }
7419
7420 /* Record the mapping between SSA_NAMEs and statements. */
7421 vect_record_grouped_load_vectors (stmt, dr_chain);
7422 }
7423 else
7424 {
7425 for (i = 0; i < vec_num; i++)
7426 {
7427 if (i > 0)
7428 dataref_ptr = bump_vector_ptr (dataref_ptr, ptr_incr, gsi,
7429 stmt, NULL_TREE);
7430
7431 /* 2. Create the vector-load in the loop. */
7432 switch (alignment_support_scheme)
7433 {
7434 case dr_aligned:
7435 case dr_unaligned_supported:
7436 {
7437 unsigned int align, misalign;
7438
7439 data_ref
7440 = fold_build2 (MEM_REF, vectype, dataref_ptr,
7441 dataref_offset
7442 ? dataref_offset
7443 : build_int_cst (ref_type, 0));
7444 align = TYPE_ALIGN_UNIT (vectype);
7445 if (alignment_support_scheme == dr_aligned)
7446 {
7447 gcc_assert (aligned_access_p (first_dr));
7448 misalign = 0;
7449 }
7450 else if (DR_MISALIGNMENT (first_dr) == -1)
7451 {
7452 if (DR_VECT_AUX (first_dr)->base_element_aligned)
7453 align = TYPE_ALIGN_UNIT (elem_type);
7454 else
7455 align = (get_object_alignment (DR_REF (first_dr))
7456 / BITS_PER_UNIT);
7457 misalign = 0;
7458 TREE_TYPE (data_ref)
7459 = build_aligned_type (TREE_TYPE (data_ref),
7460 align * BITS_PER_UNIT);
7461 }
7462 else
7463 {
7464 TREE_TYPE (data_ref)
7465 = build_aligned_type (TREE_TYPE (data_ref),
7466 TYPE_ALIGN (elem_type));
7467 misalign = DR_MISALIGNMENT (first_dr);
7468 }
7469 if (dataref_offset == NULL_TREE
7470 && TREE_CODE (dataref_ptr) == SSA_NAME)
7471 set_ptr_info_alignment (get_ptr_info (dataref_ptr),
7472 align, misalign);
7473 break;
7474 }
7475 case dr_explicit_realign:
7476 {
7477 tree ptr, bump;
7478
7479 tree vs = size_int (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype));
7480
7481 if (compute_in_loop)
7482 msq = vect_setup_realignment (first_stmt, gsi,
7483 &realignment_token,
