7484 dr_explicit_realign,
7485 dataref_ptr, NULL);
7486
7487 if (TREE_CODE (dataref_ptr) == SSA_NAME)
7488 ptr = copy_ssa_name (dataref_ptr);
7489 else
7490 ptr = make_ssa_name (TREE_TYPE (dataref_ptr));
7491 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign
7492 (ptr, BIT_AND_EXPR, dataref_ptr,
7493 build_int_cst
7494 (TREE_TYPE (dataref_ptr),
7495 -(HOST_WIDE_INT)TYPE_ALIGN_UNIT (vectype)));
7496 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
7497 data_ref
7498 = build2 (MEM_REF, vectype, ptr,
7499 build_int_cst (ref_type, 0));
7500 vec_dest = vect_create_destination_var (scalar_dest,
7501 vectype);
7502 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (vec_dest, data_ref);
7503 new_temp = make_ssa_name (vec_dest, new_stmt);
7504 gimple_assign_set_lhs (new_stmt, new_temp);
7505 gimple_set_vdef (new_stmt, gimple_vdef (stmt));
7506 gimple_set_vuse (new_stmt, gimple_vuse (stmt));
7507 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
7508 msq = new_temp;
7509
7510 bump = size_binop (MULT_EXPR, vs,
7511 TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (elem_type));
7512 bump = size_binop (MINUS_EXPR, bump, size_one_node);
7513 ptr = bump_vector_ptr (dataref_ptr, NULL, gsi, stmt, bump);
7514 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign
7515 (NULL_TREE, BIT_AND_EXPR, ptr,
7516 build_int_cst
7517 (TREE_TYPE (ptr),
7518 -(HOST_WIDE_INT)TYPE_ALIGN_UNIT (vectype)));
7519 ptr = copy_ssa_name (ptr, new_stmt);
7520 gimple_assign_set_lhs (new_stmt, ptr);
7521 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
7522 data_ref
7523 = build2 (MEM_REF, vectype, ptr,
7524 build_int_cst (ref_type, 0));
7525 break;
7526 }
7527 case dr_explicit_realign_optimized:
7528 if (TREE_CODE (dataref_ptr) == SSA_NAME)
7529 new_temp = copy_ssa_name (dataref_ptr);
7530 else
7531 new_temp = make_ssa_name (TREE_TYPE (dataref_ptr));
7532 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign
7533 (new_temp, BIT_AND_EXPR, dataref_ptr,
7534 build_int_cst
7535 (TREE_TYPE (dataref_ptr),
7536 -(HOST_WIDE_INT)TYPE_ALIGN_UNIT (vectype)));
7537 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
7538 data_ref
7539 = build2 (MEM_REF, vectype, new_temp,
7540 build_int_cst (ref_type, 0));
7541 break;
7542 default:
7543 gcc_unreachable ();
7544 }
7545 vec_dest = vect_create_destination_var (scalar_dest, vectype);
7546 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (vec_dest, data_ref);
7547 new_temp = make_ssa_name (vec_dest, new_stmt);
7548 gimple_assign_set_lhs (new_stmt, new_temp);
7549 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
7550
7551 /* 3. Handle explicit realignment if necessary/supported.
7552 Create in loop:
7553 vec_dest = realign_load (msq, lsq, realignment_token) */
7554 if (alignment_support_scheme == dr_explicit_realign_optimized
7555 || alignment_support_scheme == dr_explicit_realign)
7556 {
7557 lsq = gimple_assign_lhs (new_stmt);
7558 if (!realignment_token)
7559 realignment_token = dataref_ptr;
7560 vec_dest = vect_create_destination_var (scalar_dest, vectype);
7561 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (vec_dest, REALIGN_LOAD_EXPR,
7562 msq, lsq, realignment_token);
7563 new_temp = make_ssa_name (vec_dest, new_stmt);
7564 gimple_assign_set_lhs (new_stmt, new_temp);
7565 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
7566
7567 if (alignment_support_scheme == dr_explicit_realign_optimized)
7568 {
7569 gcc_assert (phi);
7570 if (i == vec_num - 1 && j == ncopies - 1)
7571 add_phi_arg (phi, lsq,
7572 loop_latch_edge (containing_loop),
7573 UNKNOWN_LOCATION);
7574 msq = lsq;
7575 }
7576 }
7577
7578 /* 4. Handle invariant-load. */
7579 if (inv_p && !bb_vinfo)
7580 {
7581 gcc_assert (!grouped_load);
7582 /* If we have versioned for aliasing or the loop doesn't
7583 have any data dependencies that would preclude this,
7584 then we are sure this is a loop invariant load and
7585 thus we can insert it on the preheader edge. */
7586 if (LOOP_VINFO_NO_DATA_DEPENDENCIES (loop_vinfo)
7587 && !nested_in_vect_loop
7588 && hoist_defs_of_uses (stmt, loop))
7589 {
7590 if (dump_enabled_p ())
7591 {
7592 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
7593 "hoisting out of the vectorized "
7594 "loop: ");
7595 dump_gimple_stmt (MSG_NOTE, TDF_SLIM, stmt, 0);
7596 }
7597 tree tem = copy_ssa_name (scalar_dest);
7598 gsi_insert_on_edge_immediate
7599 (loop_preheader_edge (loop),
7600 gimple_build_assign (tem,
7601 unshare_expr
7602 (gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt))));
7603 new_temp = vect_init_vector (stmt, tem, vectype, NULL);
7604 new_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (new_temp);
7605 set_vinfo_for_stmt (new_stmt,
7606 new_stmt_vec_info (new_stmt, vinfo));
7607 }
7608 else
7609 {
7610 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi2 = *gsi;
7611 gsi_next (&gsi2);
7612 new_temp = vect_init_vector (stmt, scalar_dest,
7613 vectype, &gsi2);
7614 new_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (new_temp);
7615 }
7616 }
7617
7618 if (memory_access_type == VMAT_CONTIGUOUS_REVERSE)
7619 {
7620 tree perm_mask = perm_mask_for_reverse (vectype);
7621 new_temp = permute_vec_elements (new_temp, new_temp,
7622 perm_mask, stmt, gsi);
7623 new_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (new_temp);
7624 }
7625
7626 /* Collect vector loads and later create their permutation in
7627 vect_transform_grouped_load (). */
7628 if (grouped_load || slp_perm)
7629 dr_chain.quick_push (new_temp);
7630
7631 /* Store vector loads in the corresponding SLP_NODE. */
7632 if (slp && !slp_perm)
7633 SLP_TREE_VEC_STMTS (slp_node).quick_push (new_stmt);
7634
7635 /* With SLP permutation we load the gaps as well, without
7636 we need to skip the gaps after we manage to fully load
7637 all elements. group_gap_adj is GROUP_SIZE here. */
7638 group_elt += nunits;
7639 if (group_gap_adj != 0 && ! slp_perm
7640 && group_elt == group_size - group_gap_adj)
7641 {
7642 bool ovf;
7643 tree bump
7644 = wide_int_to_tree (sizetype,
7645 wi::smul (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (elem_type),
7646 group_gap_adj, &ovf));
7647 dataref_ptr = bump_vector_ptr (dataref_ptr, ptr_incr, gsi,
7648 stmt, bump);
7649 group_elt = 0;
7650 }
7651 }
7652 /* Bump the vector pointer to account for a gap or for excess
7653 elements loaded for a permuted SLP load. */
7654 if (group_gap_adj != 0 && slp_perm)
7655 {
7656 bool ovf;
7657 tree bump
7658 = wide_int_to_tree (sizetype,
7659 wi::smul (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (elem_type),
7660 group_gap_adj, &ovf));
7661 dataref_ptr = bump_vector_ptr (dataref_ptr, ptr_incr, gsi,
7662 stmt, bump);
7663 }
7664 }
7665
7666 if (slp && !slp_perm)
7667 continue;
7668
7669 if (slp_perm)
7670 {
7671 unsigned n_perms;
7672 if (!vect_transform_slp_perm_load (slp_node, dr_chain, gsi, vf,
7673 slp_node_instance, false,
7674 &n_perms))
7675 {
7676 dr_chain.release ();
7677 return false;
7678 }
7679 }
7680 else
7681 {
7682 if (grouped_load)
7683 {
7684 if (memory_access_type != VMAT_LOAD_STORE_LANES)
7685 vect_transform_grouped_load (stmt, dr_chain, group_size, gsi);
7686 *vec_stmt = STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info);
7687 }
7688 else
7689 {
7690 if (j == 0)
7691 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info) = *vec_stmt = new_stmt;
7692 else
7693 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (prev_stmt_info) = new_stmt;
7694 prev_stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (new_stmt);
7695 }
7696 }
7697 dr_chain.release ();
7698 }
7699
7700 return true;
7701}
7702
7703/* Function vect_is_simple_cond.
7704
7705 Input:
7706 LOOP - the loop that is being vectorized.
7707 COND - Condition that is checked for simple use.
7708
7709 Output:
7710 *COMP_VECTYPE - the vector type for the comparison.
7711
7712 Returns whether a COND can be vectorized. Checks whether
7713 condition operands are supportable using vec_is_simple_use. */
7714
7715static bool
7716vect_is_simple_cond (tree cond, vec_info *vinfo, tree *comp_vectype)
7717{
7718 tree lhs, rhs;
7719 enum vect_def_type dt;
7720 tree vectype1 = NULL_TREE, vectype2 = NULL_TREE;
7721
7722 /* Mask case. */
7723 if (TREE_CODE (cond) == SSA_NAME
7724 && VECT_SCALAR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (cond)))
7725 {
7726 gimple *lhs_def_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (cond);
7727 if (!vect_is_simple_use (cond, vinfo, &lhs_def_stmt,
7728 &dt, comp_vectype)
7729 || !*comp_vectype
7730 || !VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (*comp_vectype))
7731 return false;
7732 return true;
7733 }
7734
7735 if (!COMPARISON_CLASS_P (cond))
7736 return false;
7737
7738 lhs = TREE_OPERAND (cond, 0);
7739 rhs = TREE_OPERAND (cond, 1);
7740
7741 if (TREE_CODE (lhs) == SSA_NAME)
7742 {
7743 gimple *lhs_def_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (lhs);
7744 if (!vect_is_simple_use (lhs, vinfo, &lhs_def_stmt, &dt, &vectype1))
7745 return false;
7746 }
7747 else if (TREE_CODE (lhs) != INTEGER_CST && TREE_CODE (lhs) != REAL_CST
7748 && TREE_CODE (lhs) != FIXED_CST)
7749 return false;
7750
7751 if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == SSA_NAME)
7752 {
7753 gimple *rhs_def_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (rhs);
7754 if (!vect_is_simple_use (rhs, vinfo, &rhs_def_stmt, &dt, &vectype2))
7755 return false;
7756 }
7757 else if (TREE_CODE (rhs) != INTEGER_CST && TREE_CODE (rhs) != REAL_CST
7758 && TREE_CODE (rhs) != FIXED_CST)
7759 return false;
7760
7761 if (vectype1 && vectype2
7762 && TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype1) != TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype2))
7763 return false;
7764
7765 *comp_vectype = vectype1 ? vectype1 : vectype2;
7766 return true;
7767}
7768
7769/* vectorizable_condition.
7770
7771 Check if STMT is conditional modify expression that can be vectorized.
7772 If VEC_STMT is also passed, vectorize the STMT: create a vectorized
7773 stmt using VEC_COND_EXPR to replace it, put it in VEC_STMT, and insert it
7774 at GSI.
7775
7776 When STMT is vectorized as nested cycle, REDUC_DEF is the vector variable
7777 to be used at REDUC_INDEX (in then clause if REDUC_INDEX is 1, and in
7778 else clause if it is 2).
7779
7780 Return FALSE if not a vectorizable STMT, TRUE otherwise. */
7781
7782bool
7783vectorizable_condition (gimple *stmt, gimple_stmt_iterator *gsi,
7784 gimple **vec_stmt, tree reduc_def, int reduc_index,
7785 slp_tree slp_node)
7786{
7787 tree scalar_dest = NULL_TREE;
7788 tree vec_dest = NULL_TREE;
7789 tree cond_expr, cond_expr0 = NULL_TREE, cond_expr1 = NULL_TREE;
7790 tree then_clause, else_clause;
7791 stmt_vec_info stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (stmt);
7792 tree comp_vectype = NULL_TREE;
7793 tree vec_cond_lhs = NULL_TREE, vec_cond_rhs = NULL_TREE;
7794 tree vec_then_clause = NULL_TREE, vec_else_clause = NULL_TREE;
7795 tree vec_compare;
7796 tree new_temp;
7797 loop_vec_info loop_vinfo = STMT_VINFO_LOOP_VINFO (stmt_info);
7798 enum vect_def_type dt, dts[4];
7799 int ncopies;
7800 enum tree_code code, cond_code, bitop1 = NOP_EXPR, bitop2 = NOP_EXPR;
7801 stmt_vec_info prev_stmt_info = NULL;
7802 int i, j;
7803 bb_vec_info bb_vinfo = STMT_VINFO_BB_VINFO (stmt_info);
7804 vec<tree> vec_oprnds0 = vNULL;
7805 vec<tree> vec_oprnds1 = vNULL;
7806 vec<tree> vec_oprnds2 = vNULL;
7807 vec<tree> vec_oprnds3 = vNULL;
7808 tree vec_cmp_type;
7809 bool masked = false;
7810
7811 if (reduc_index && STMT_SLP_TYPE (stmt_info))
7812 return false;
7813
7814 if (STMT_VINFO_VEC_REDUCTION_TYPE (stmt_info) == TREE_CODE_REDUCTION)
7815 {
7816 if (!STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT_P (stmt_info) && !bb_vinfo)
7817 return false;
7818
7819 if (STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (stmt_info) != vect_internal_def
7820 && !(STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (stmt_info) == vect_nested_cycle
7821 && reduc_def))
7822 return false;
7823
7824 /* FORNOW: not yet supported. */
7825 if (STMT_VINFO_LIVE_P (stmt_info))
7826 {
7827 if (dump_enabled_p ())
7828 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
7829 "value used after loop.\n");
7830 return false;
7831 }
7832 }
7833
7834 /* Is vectorizable conditional operation? */
7835 if (!is_gimple_assign (stmt))
7836 return false;
7837
7838 code = gimple_assign_rhs_code (stmt);
7839
7840 if (code != COND_EXPR)
7841 return false;
7842
7843 tree vectype = STMT_VINFO_VECTYPE (stmt_info);
7844 int nunits = TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype);
7845 tree vectype1 = NULL_TREE, vectype2 = NULL_TREE;
7846
7847 if (slp_node)
7848 ncopies = 1;
7849 else
7850 ncopies = LOOP_VINFO_VECT_FACTOR (loop_vinfo) / nunits;
7851
7852 gcc_assert (ncopies >= 1);
7853 if (reduc_index && ncopies > 1)
7854 return false; /* FORNOW */
7855
7856 cond_expr = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
7857 then_clause = gimple_assign_rhs2 (stmt);
7858 else_clause = gimple_assign_rhs3 (stmt);
7859
7860 if (!vect_is_simple_cond (cond_expr, stmt_info->vinfo, &comp_vectype)
7861 || !comp_vectype)
7862 return false;
7863
7864 gimple *def_stmt;
7865 if (!vect_is_simple_use (then_clause, stmt_info->vinfo, &def_stmt, &dt,
7866 &vectype1))
7867 return false;
7868 if (!vect_is_simple_use (else_clause, stmt_info->vinfo, &def_stmt, &dt,
7869 &vectype2))
7870 return false;
7871
7872 if (vectype1 && !useless_type_conversion_p (vectype, vectype1))
7873 return false;
7874
7875 if (vectype2 && !useless_type_conversion_p (vectype, vectype2))
7876 return false;
7877
7878 masked = !COMPARISON_CLASS_P (cond_expr);
7879 vec_cmp_type = build_same_sized_truth_vector_type (comp_vectype);
7880
7881 if (vec_cmp_type == NULL_TREE)
7882 return false;
7883
7884 cond_code = TREE_CODE (cond_expr);
7885 if (!masked)
7886 {
7887 cond_expr0 = TREE_OPERAND (cond_expr, 0);
7888 cond_expr1 = TREE_OPERAND (cond_expr, 1);
7889 }
7890
7891 if (!masked && VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (comp_vectype))
7892 {
7893 /* Boolean values may have another representation in vectors
7894 and therefore we prefer bit operations over comparison for
7895 them (which also works for scalar masks). We store opcodes
7896 to use in bitop1 and bitop2. Statement is vectorized as
7897 BITOP2 (rhs1 BITOP1 rhs2) or rhs1 BITOP2 (BITOP1 rhs2)
7898 depending on bitop1 and bitop2 arity. */
7899 switch (cond_code)
7900 {
7901 case GT_EXPR:
7902 bitop1 = BIT_NOT_EXPR;
7903 bitop2 = BIT_AND_EXPR;
7904 break;
7905 case GE_EXPR:
7906 bitop1 = BIT_NOT_EXPR;
7907 bitop2 = BIT_IOR_EXPR;
7908 break;
7909 case LT_EXPR:
7910 bitop1 = BIT_NOT_EXPR;
7911 bitop2 = BIT_AND_EXPR;
7912 std::swap (cond_expr0, cond_expr1);
7913 break;
7914 case LE_EXPR:
7915 bitop1 = BIT_NOT_EXPR;
7916 bitop2 = BIT_IOR_EXPR;
7917 std::swap (cond_expr0, cond_expr1);
7918 break;
7919 case NE_EXPR:
7920 bitop1 = BIT_XOR_EXPR;
7921 break;
7922 case EQ_EXPR:
7923 bitop1 = BIT_XOR_EXPR;
7924 bitop2 = BIT_NOT_EXPR;
7925 break;
7926 default:
7927 return false;
7928 }
7929 cond_code = SSA_NAME;
7930 }
7931
7932 if (!vec_stmt)
7933 {
7934 STMT_VINFO_TYPE (stmt_info) = condition_vec_info_type;
7935 if (bitop1 != NOP_EXPR)
7936 {
7937 machine_mode mode = TYPE_MODE (comp_vectype);
7938 optab optab;
7939
7940 optab = optab_for_tree_code (bitop1, comp_vectype, optab_default);
7941 if (!optab || optab_handler (optab, mode) == CODE_FOR_nothing)
7942 return false;
7943
7944 if (bitop2 != NOP_EXPR)
7945 {
7946 optab = optab_for_tree_code (bitop2, comp_vectype,
7947 optab_default);
7948 if (!optab || optab_handler (optab, mode) == CODE_FOR_nothing)
7949 return false;
7950 }
7951 }
7952 return expand_vec_cond_expr_p (vectype, comp_vectype,
7953 cond_code);
7954 }
7955
7956 /* Transform. */
7957
7958 if (!slp_node)
7959 {
7960 vec_oprnds0.create (1);
7961 vec_oprnds1.create (1);
7962 vec_oprnds2.create (1);
7963 vec_oprnds3.create (1);
7964 }
7965
7966 /* Handle def. */
7967 scalar_dest = gimple_assign_lhs (stmt);
7968 vec_dest = vect_create_destination_var (scalar_dest, vectype);
7969
7970 /* Handle cond expr. */
7971 for (j = 0; j < ncopies; j++)
7972 {
7973 gassign *new_stmt = NULL;
7974 if (j == 0)
7975 {
7976 if (slp_node)
7977 {
7978 auto_vec<tree, 4> ops;
7979 auto_vec<vec<tree>, 4> vec_defs;
7980
7981 if (masked)
7982 ops.safe_push (cond_expr);
7983 else
7984 {
7985 ops.safe_push (cond_expr0);
7986 ops.safe_push (cond_expr1);
7987 }
7988 ops.safe_push (then_clause);
7989 ops.safe_push (else_clause);
7990 vect_get_slp_defs (ops, slp_node, &vec_defs, -1);
7991 vec_oprnds3 = vec_defs.pop ();
7992 vec_oprnds2 = vec_defs.pop ();
7993 if (!masked)
7994 vec_oprnds1 = vec_defs.pop ();
7995 vec_oprnds0 = vec_defs.pop ();
7996 }
7997 else
7998 {
7999 gimple *gtemp;
8000 if (masked)
8001 {
8002 vec_cond_lhs
8003 = vect_get_vec_def_for_operand (cond_expr, stmt,
8004 comp_vectype);
8005 vect_is_simple_use (cond_expr, stmt_info->vinfo,
8006 &gtemp, &dts[0]);
8007 }
8008 else
8009 {
8010 vec_cond_lhs
8011 = vect_get_vec_def_for_operand (cond_expr0,
8012 stmt, comp_vectype);
8013 vect_is_simple_use (cond_expr0, loop_vinfo, &gtemp, &dts[0]);
8014
8015 vec_cond_rhs
8016 = vect_get_vec_def_for_operand (cond_expr1,
8017 stmt, comp_vectype);
8018 vect_is_simple_use (cond_expr1, loop_vinfo, &gtemp, &dts[1]);
8019 }
8020 if (reduc_index == 1)
8021 vec_then_clause = reduc_def;
8022 else
8023 {
8024 vec_then_clause = vect_get_vec_def_for_operand (then_clause,
8025 stmt);
8026 vect_is_simple_use (then_clause, loop_vinfo,
8027 &gtemp, &dts[2]);
8028 }
8029 if (reduc_index == 2)
8030 vec_else_clause = reduc_def;
8031 else
8032 {
8033 vec_else_clause = vect_get_vec_def_for_operand (else_clause,
8034 stmt);
8035 vect_is_simple_use (else_clause, loop_vinfo, &gtemp, &dts[3]);
8036 }
8037 }
8038 }
8039 else
8040 {
8041 vec_cond_lhs
8042 = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (dts[0],
8043 vec_oprnds0.pop ());
8044 if (!masked)
8045 vec_cond_rhs
8046 = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (dts[1],
8047 vec_oprnds1.pop ());
8048
8049 vec_then_clause = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (dts[2],
8050 vec_oprnds2.pop ());
8051 vec_else_clause = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (dts[3],
8052 vec_oprnds3.pop ());
8053 }
8054
8055 if (!slp_node)
8056 {
8057 vec_oprnds0.quick_push (vec_cond_lhs);
8058 if (!masked)
8059 vec_oprnds1.quick_push (vec_cond_rhs);
8060 vec_oprnds2.quick_push (vec_then_clause);
8061 vec_oprnds3.quick_push (vec_else_clause);
8062 }
8063
8064 /* Arguments are ready. Create the new vector stmt. */
8065 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (vec_oprnds0, i, vec_cond_lhs)
8066 {
8067 vec_then_clause = vec_oprnds2[i];
8068 vec_else_clause = vec_oprnds3[i];
8069
8070 if (masked)
8071 vec_compare = vec_cond_lhs;
8072 else
8073 {
8074 vec_cond_rhs = vec_oprnds1[i];
8075 if (bitop1 == NOP_EXPR)
8076 vec_compare = build2 (cond_code, vec_cmp_type,
8077 vec_cond_lhs, vec_cond_rhs);
8078 else
8079 {
8080 new_temp = make_ssa_name (vec_cmp_type);
8081 if (bitop1 == BIT_NOT_EXPR)
8082 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (new_temp, bitop1,
8083 vec_cond_rhs);
8084 else
8085 new_stmt
8086 = gimple_build_assign (new_temp, bitop1, vec_cond_lhs,
8087 vec_cond_rhs);
8088 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
8089 if (bitop2 == NOP_EXPR)
8090 vec_compare = new_temp;
8091 else if (bitop2 == BIT_NOT_EXPR)
8092 {
8093 /* Instead of doing ~x ? y : z do x ? z : y. */
8094 vec_compare = new_temp;
8095 std::swap (vec_then_clause, vec_else_clause);
8096 }
8097 else
8098 {
8099 vec_compare = make_ssa_name (vec_cmp_type);
8100 new_stmt
8101 = gimple_build_assign (vec_compare, bitop2,
8102 vec_cond_lhs, new_temp);
8103 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
8104 }
8105 }
8106 }
8107 new_temp = make_ssa_name (vec_dest);
8108 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (new_temp, VEC_COND_EXPR,
8109 vec_compare, vec_then_clause,
8110 vec_else_clause);
8111 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
8112 if (slp_node)
8113 SLP_TREE_VEC_STMTS (slp_node).quick_push (new_stmt);
8114 }
8115
8116 if (slp_node)
8117 continue;
8118
8119 if (j == 0)
8120 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info) = *vec_stmt = new_stmt;
8121 else
8122 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (prev_stmt_info) = new_stmt;
8123
8124 prev_stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (new_stmt);
8125 }
8126
8127 vec_oprnds0.release ();
8128 vec_oprnds1.release ();
8129 vec_oprnds2.release ();
8130 vec_oprnds3.release ();
8131
8132 return true;
8133}
8134
8135/* vectorizable_comparison.
8136
8137 Check if STMT is comparison expression that can be vectorized.
8138 If VEC_STMT is also passed, vectorize the STMT: create a vectorized
8139 comparison, put it in VEC_STMT, and insert it at GSI.
8140
8141 Return FALSE if not a vectorizable STMT, TRUE otherwise. */
8142
8143static bool
8144vectorizable_comparison (gimple *stmt, gimple_stmt_iterator *gsi,
8145 gimple **vec_stmt, tree reduc_def,
8146 slp_tree slp_node)
8147{
8148 tree lhs, rhs1, rhs2;
8149 stmt_vec_info stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (stmt);
8150 tree vectype1 = NULL_TREE, vectype2 = NULL_TREE;
8151 tree vectype = STMT_VINFO_VECTYPE (stmt_info);
8152 tree vec_rhs1 = NULL_TREE, vec_rhs2 = NULL_TREE;
8153 tree new_temp;
8154 loop_vec_info loop_vinfo = STMT_VINFO_LOOP_VINFO (stmt_info);
8155 enum vect_def_type dts[2] = {vect_unknown_def_type, vect_unknown_def_type};
8156 unsigned nunits;
8157 int ncopies;
8158 enum tree_code code, bitop1 = NOP_EXPR, bitop2 = NOP_EXPR;
8159 stmt_vec_info prev_stmt_info = NULL;
8160 int i, j;
8161 bb_vec_info bb_vinfo = STMT_VINFO_BB_VINFO (stmt_info);
8162 vec<tree> vec_oprnds0 = vNULL;
8163 vec<tree> vec_oprnds1 = vNULL;
8164 gimple *def_stmt;
8165 tree mask_type;
8166 tree mask;
8167
8168 if (!STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT_P (stmt_info) && !bb_vinfo)
8169 return false;
8170
8171 if (!vectype || !VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (vectype))
8172 return false;
8173
8174 mask_type = vectype;
8175 nunits = TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype);
8176
8177 if (slp_node)
8178 ncopies = 1;
8179 else
8180 ncopies = LOOP_VINFO_VECT_FACTOR (loop_vinfo) / nunits;
8181
8182 gcc_assert (ncopies >= 1);
8183 if (STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (stmt_info) != vect_internal_def
8184 && !(STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (stmt_info) == vect_nested_cycle
8185 && reduc_def))
8186 return false;
8187
8188 if (STMT_VINFO_LIVE_P (stmt_info))
8189 {
8190 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8191 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
8192 "value used after loop.\n");
8193 return false;
8194 }
8195
8196 if (!is_gimple_assign (stmt))
8197 return false;
8198
8199 code = gimple_assign_rhs_code (stmt);
8200
8201 if (TREE_CODE_CLASS (code) != tcc_comparison)
8202 return false;
8203
8204 rhs1 = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
8205 rhs2 = gimple_assign_rhs2 (stmt);
8206
8207 if (!vect_is_simple_use (rhs1, stmt_info->vinfo, &def_stmt,
8208 &dts[0], &vectype1))
8209 return false;
8210
8211 if (!vect_is_simple_use (rhs2, stmt_info->vinfo, &def_stmt,
8212 &dts[1], &vectype2))
8213 return false;
8214
8215 if (vectype1 && vectype2
8216 && TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype1) != TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype2))
8217 return false;
8218
8219 vectype = vectype1 ? vectype1 : vectype2;
8220
8221 /* Invariant comparison. */
8222 if (!vectype)
8223 {
8224 vectype = get_vectype_for_scalar_type (TREE_TYPE (rhs1));
8225 if (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype) != nunits)
8226 return false;
8227 }
8228 else if (nunits != TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype))
8229 return false;
8230
8231 /* Can't compare mask and non-mask types. */
8232 if (vectype1 && vectype2
8233 && (VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (vectype1) ^ VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (vectype2)))
8234 return false;
8235
8236 /* Boolean values may have another representation in vectors
8237 and therefore we prefer bit operations over comparison for
8238 them (which also works for scalar masks). We store opcodes
8239 to use in bitop1 and bitop2. Statement is vectorized as
8240 BITOP2 (rhs1 BITOP1 rhs2) or
8241 rhs1 BITOP2 (BITOP1 rhs2)
8242 depending on bitop1 and bitop2 arity. */
8243 if (VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (vectype))
8244 {
8245 if (code == GT_EXPR)
8246 {
8247 bitop1 = BIT_NOT_EXPR;
8248 bitop2 = BIT_AND_EXPR;
8249 }
8250 else if (code == GE_EXPR)
8251 {
8252 bitop1 = BIT_NOT_EXPR;
8253 bitop2 = BIT_IOR_EXPR;
8254 }
8255 else if (code == LT_EXPR)
8256 {
8257 bitop1 = BIT_NOT_EXPR;
8258 bitop2 = BIT_AND_EXPR;
8259 std::swap (rhs1, rhs2);
8260 std::swap (dts[0], dts[1]);
8261 }
8262 else if (code == LE_EXPR)
8263 {
8264 bitop1 = BIT_NOT_EXPR;
8265 bitop2 = BIT_IOR_EXPR;
8266 std::swap (rhs1, rhs2);
8267 std::swap (dts[0], dts[1]);
8268 }
8269 else
8270 {
8271 bitop1 = BIT_XOR_EXPR;
8272 if (code == EQ_EXPR)
8273 bitop2 = BIT_NOT_EXPR;
8274 }
8275 }
8276
8277 if (!vec_stmt)
8278 {
8279 STMT_VINFO_TYPE (stmt_info) = comparison_vec_info_type;
8280 vect_model_simple_cost (stmt_info, ncopies * (1 + (bitop2 != NOP_EXPR)),
8281 dts, NULL, NULL);
8282 if (bitop1 == NOP_EXPR)
8283 return expand_vec_cmp_expr_p (vectype, mask_type, code);
8284 else
8285 {
8286 machine_mode mode = TYPE_MODE (vectype);
8287 optab optab;
8288
8289 optab = optab_for_tree_code (bitop1, vectype, optab_default);
8290 if (!optab || optab_handler (optab, mode) == CODE_FOR_nothing)
8291 return false;
8292
8293 if (bitop2 != NOP_EXPR)
8294 {
8295 optab = optab_for_tree_code (bitop2, vectype, optab_default);
8296 if (!optab || optab_handler (optab, mode) == CODE_FOR_nothing)
8297 return false;
8298 }
8299 return true;
8300 }
8301 }
8302
8303 /* Transform. */
8304 if (!slp_node)
8305 {
8306 vec_oprnds0.create (1);
8307 vec_oprnds1.create (1);
8308 }
8309
8310 /* Handle def. */
8311 lhs = gimple_assign_lhs (stmt);
8312 mask = vect_create_destination_var (lhs, mask_type);
8313
8314 /* Handle cmp expr. */
8315 for (j = 0; j < ncopies; j++)
8316 {
8317 gassign *new_stmt = NULL;
8318 if (j == 0)
8319 {
8320 if (slp_node)
8321 {
8322 auto_vec<tree, 2> ops;
8323 auto_vec<vec<tree>, 2> vec_defs;
8324
8325 ops.safe_push (rhs1);
8326 ops.safe_push (rhs2);
8327 vect_get_slp_defs (ops, slp_node, &vec_defs, -1);
8328 vec_oprnds1 = vec_defs.pop ();
8329 vec_oprnds0 = vec_defs.pop ();
8330 }
8331 else
8332 {
8333 vec_rhs1 = vect_get_vec_def_for_operand (rhs1, stmt, vectype);
8334 vec_rhs2 = vect_get_vec_def_for_operand (rhs2, stmt, vectype);
8335 }
8336 }
8337 else
8338 {
8339 vec_rhs1 = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (dts[0],
8340 vec_oprnds0.pop ());
8341 vec_rhs2 = vect_get_vec_def_for_stmt_copy (dts[1],
8342 vec_oprnds1.pop ());
8343 }
8344
8345 if (!slp_node)
8346 {
8347 vec_oprnds0.quick_push (vec_rhs1);
8348 vec_oprnds1.quick_push (vec_rhs2);
8349 }
8350
8351 /* Arguments are ready. Create the new vector stmt. */
8352 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (vec_oprnds0, i, vec_rhs1)
8353 {
8354 vec_rhs2 = vec_oprnds1[i];
8355
8356 new_temp = make_ssa_name (mask);
8357 if (bitop1 == NOP_EXPR)
8358 {
8359 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (new_temp, code,
8360 vec_rhs1, vec_rhs2);
8361 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
8362 }
8363 else
8364 {
8365 if (bitop1 == BIT_NOT_EXPR)
8366 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (new_temp, bitop1, vec_rhs2);
8367 else
8368 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (new_temp, bitop1, vec_rhs1,
8369 vec_rhs2);
8370 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
8371 if (bitop2 != NOP_EXPR)
8372 {
8373 tree res = make_ssa_name (mask);
8374 if (bitop2 == BIT_NOT_EXPR)
8375 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (res, bitop2, new_temp);
8376 else
8377 new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (res, bitop2, vec_rhs1,
8378 new_temp);
8379 vect_finish_stmt_generation (stmt, new_stmt, gsi);
8380 }
8381 }
8382 if (slp_node)
8383 SLP_TREE_VEC_STMTS (slp_node).quick_push (new_stmt);
8384 }
8385
8386 if (slp_node)
8387 continue;
8388
8389 if (j == 0)
8390 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info) = *vec_stmt = new_stmt;
8391 else
8392 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (prev_stmt_info) = new_stmt;
8393
8394 prev_stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (new_stmt);
8395 }
8396
8397 vec_oprnds0.release ();
8398 vec_oprnds1.release ();
8399
8400 return true;
8401}
8402
8403/* Make sure the statement is vectorizable. */
8404
8405bool
8406vect_analyze_stmt (gimple *stmt, bool *need_to_vectorize, slp_tree node)
8407{
8408 stmt_vec_info stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (stmt);
8409 bb_vec_info bb_vinfo = STMT_VINFO_BB_VINFO (stmt_info);
8410 enum vect_relevant relevance = STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT (stmt_info);
8411 bool ok;
8412 tree scalar_type, vectype;
8413 gimple *pattern_stmt;
8414 gimple_seq pattern_def_seq;
8415
8416 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8417 {
8418 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location, "==> examining statement: ");
8419 dump_gimple_stmt (MSG_NOTE, TDF_SLIM, stmt, 0);
8420 }
8421
8422 if (gimple_has_volatile_ops (stmt))
8423 {
8424 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8425 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
8426 "not vectorized: stmt has volatile operands\n");
8427
8428 return false;
8429 }
8430
8431 /* Skip stmts that do not need to be vectorized. In loops this is expected
8432 to include:
8433 - the COND_EXPR which is the loop exit condition
8434 - any LABEL_EXPRs in the loop
8435 - computations that are used only for array indexing or loop control.
8436 In basic blocks we only analyze statements that are a part of some SLP
8437 instance, therefore, all the statements are relevant.
8438
8439 Pattern statement needs to be analyzed instead of the original statement
8440 if the original statement is not relevant. Otherwise, we analyze both
8441 statements. In basic blocks we are called from some SLP instance
8442 traversal, don't analyze pattern stmts instead, the pattern stmts
8443 already will be part of SLP instance. */
8444
8445 pattern_stmt = STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (stmt_info);
8446 if (!STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT_P (stmt_info)
8447 && !STMT_VINFO_LIVE_P (stmt_info))
8448 {
8449 if (STMT_VINFO_IN_PATTERN_P (stmt_info)
8450 && pattern_stmt
8451 && (STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT_P (vinfo_for_stmt (pattern_stmt))
8452 || STMT_VINFO_LIVE_P (vinfo_for_stmt (pattern_stmt))))
8453 {
8454 /* Analyze PATTERN_STMT instead of the original stmt. */
8455 stmt = pattern_stmt;
8456 stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (pattern_stmt);
8457 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8458 {
8459 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
8460 "==> examining pattern statement: ");
8461 dump_gimple_stmt (MSG_NOTE, TDF_SLIM, stmt, 0);
8462 }
8463 }
8464 else
8465 {
8466 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8467 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location, "irrelevant.\n");
8468
8469 return true;
8470 }
8471 }
8472 else if (STMT_VINFO_IN_PATTERN_P (stmt_info)
8473 && node == NULL
8474 && pattern_stmt
8475 && (STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT_P (vinfo_for_stmt (pattern_stmt))
8476 || STMT_VINFO_LIVE_P (vinfo_for_stmt (pattern_stmt))))
8477 {
8478 /* Analyze PATTERN_STMT too. */
8479 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8480 {
8481 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
8482 "==> examining pattern statement: ");
8483 dump_gimple_stmt (MSG_NOTE, TDF_SLIM, stmt, 0);
8484 }
8485
8486 if (!vect_analyze_stmt (pattern_stmt, need_to_vectorize, node))
8487 return false;
8488 }
8489
8490 if (is_pattern_stmt_p (stmt_info)
8491 && node == NULL
8492 && (pattern_def_seq = STMT_VINFO_PATTERN_DEF_SEQ (stmt_info)))
8493 {
8494 gimple_stmt_iterator si;
8495
8496 for (si = gsi_start (pattern_def_seq); !gsi_end_p (si); gsi_next (&si))
8497 {
8498 gimple *pattern_def_stmt = gsi_stmt (si);
8499 if (STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT_P (vinfo_for_stmt (pattern_def_stmt))
8500 || STMT_VINFO_LIVE_P (vinfo_for_stmt (pattern_def_stmt)))
8501 {
8502 /* Analyze def stmt of STMT if it's a pattern stmt. */
8503 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8504 {
8505 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
8506 "==> examining pattern def statement: ");
8507 dump_gimple_stmt (MSG_NOTE, TDF_SLIM, pattern_def_stmt, 0);
8508 }
8509
8510 if (!vect_analyze_stmt (pattern_def_stmt,
8511 need_to_vectorize, node))
8512 return false;
8513 }
8514 }
8515 }
8516
8517 switch (STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (stmt_info))
8518 {
8519 case vect_internal_def:
8520 break;
8521
8522 case vect_reduction_def:
8523 case vect_nested_cycle:
8524 gcc_assert (!bb_vinfo
8525 && (relevance == vect_used_in_outer
8526 || relevance == vect_used_in_outer_by_reduction
8527 || relevance == vect_used_by_reduction
8528 || relevance == vect_unused_in_scope
8529 || relevance == vect_used_only_live));
8530 break;
8531
8532 case vect_induction_def:
8533 case vect_constant_def:
8534 case vect_external_def:
8535 case vect_unknown_def_type:
8536 default:
8537 gcc_unreachable ();
8538 }
8539
8540 if (bb_vinfo)
8541 {
8542 gcc_assert (PURE_SLP_STMT (stmt_info));
8543
8544 /* Memory accesses already got their vector type assigned
8545 in vect_analyze_data_refs. */
8546 if (! STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (stmt_info))
8547 {
8548 scalar_type = TREE_TYPE (gimple_get_lhs (stmt));
8549 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8550 {
8551 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
8552 "get vectype for scalar type: ");
8553 dump_generic_expr (MSG_NOTE, TDF_SLIM, scalar_type);
8554 dump_printf (MSG_NOTE, "\n");
8555 }
8556
8557 vectype = get_vectype_for_scalar_type (scalar_type);
8558 if (!vectype)
8559 {
8560 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8561 {
8562 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
8563 "not SLPed: unsupported data-type ");
8564 dump_generic_expr (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, TDF_SLIM,
8565 scalar_type);
8566 dump_printf (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, "\n");
8567 }
8568 return false;
8569 }
8570
8571 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8572 {
8573 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location, "vectype: ");
8574 dump_generic_expr (MSG_NOTE, TDF_SLIM, vectype);
8575 dump_printf (MSG_NOTE, "\n");
8576 }
8577
8578 STMT_VINFO_VECTYPE (stmt_info) = vectype;
8579 }
8580 }
8581
8582 if (STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT_P (stmt_info))
8583 {
8584 gcc_assert (!VECTOR_MODE_P (TYPE_MODE (gimple_expr_type (stmt))));
8585 gcc_assert (STMT_VINFO_VECTYPE (stmt_info)
8586 || (is_gimple_call (stmt)
8587 && gimple_call_lhs (stmt) == NULL_TREE));
8588 *need_to_vectorize = true;
8589 }
8590
8591 if (PURE_SLP_STMT (stmt_info) && !node)
8592 {
8593 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
8594 "handled only by SLP analysis\n");
8595 return true;
8596 }
8597
8598 ok = true;
8599 if (!bb_vinfo
8600 && (STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT_P (stmt_info)
8601 || STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (stmt_info) == vect_reduction_def))
8602 ok = (vectorizable_simd_clone_call (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8603 || vectorizable_conversion (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8604 || vectorizable_shift (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8605 || vectorizable_operation (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8606 || vectorizable_assignment (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8607 || vectorizable_load (stmt, NULL, NULL, node, NULL)
8608 || vectorizable_call (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8609 || vectorizable_store (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8610 || vectorizable_reduction (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8611 || vectorizable_condition (stmt, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, node)
8612 || vectorizable_comparison (stmt, NULL, NULL, NULL, node));
8613 else
8614 {
8615 if (bb_vinfo)
8616 ok = (vectorizable_simd_clone_call (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8617 || vectorizable_conversion (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8618 || vectorizable_shift (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8619 || vectorizable_operation (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8620 || vectorizable_assignment (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8621 || vectorizable_load (stmt, NULL, NULL, node, NULL)
8622 || vectorizable_call (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8623 || vectorizable_store (stmt, NULL, NULL, node)
8624 || vectorizable_condition (stmt, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, node)
8625 || vectorizable_comparison (stmt, NULL, NULL, NULL, node));
8626 }
8627
8628 if (!ok)
8629 {
8630 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8631 {
8632 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
8633 "not vectorized: relevant stmt not ");
8634 dump_printf (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, "supported: ");
8635 dump_gimple_stmt (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, TDF_SLIM, stmt, 0);
8636 }
8637
8638 return false;
8639 }
8640
8641 if (bb_vinfo)
8642 return true;
8643
8644 /* Stmts that are (also) "live" (i.e. - that are used out of the loop)
8645 need extra handling, except for vectorizable reductions. */
8646 if (STMT_VINFO_LIVE_P (stmt_info)
8647 && STMT_VINFO_TYPE (stmt_info) != reduc_vec_info_type)
8648 ok = vectorizable_live_operation (stmt, NULL, NULL, -1, NULL);
8649
8650 if (!ok)
8651 {
8652 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8653 {
8654 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
8655 "not vectorized: live stmt not ");
8656 dump_printf (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, "supported: ");
8657 dump_gimple_stmt (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, TDF_SLIM, stmt, 0);
8658 }
8659
8660 return false;
8661 }
8662
8663 return true;
8664}
8665
8666
8667/* Function vect_transform_stmt.
8668
8669 Create a vectorized stmt to replace STMT, and insert it at BSI. */
8670
8671bool
8672vect_transform_stmt (gimple *stmt, gimple_stmt_iterator *gsi,
8673 bool *grouped_store, slp_tree slp_node,
8674 slp_instance slp_node_instance)
8675{
8676 bool is_store = false;
8677 gimple *vec_stmt = NULL;
8678 stmt_vec_info stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (stmt);
8679 bool done;
8680
8681 gcc_assert (slp_node || !PURE_SLP_STMT (stmt_info));
8682 gimple *old_vec_stmt = STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info);
8683
8684 switch (STMT_VINFO_TYPE (stmt_info))
8685 {
8686 case type_demotion_vec_info_type:
8687 case type_promotion_vec_info_type:
8688 case type_conversion_vec_info_type:
8689 done = vectorizable_conversion (stmt, gsi, &vec_stmt, slp_node);
8690 gcc_assert (done);
8691 break;
8692
8693 case induc_vec_info_type:
8694 gcc_assert (!slp_node);
8695 done = vectorizable_induction (stmt, gsi, &vec_stmt);
8696 gcc_assert (done);
8697 break;
8698
8699 case shift_vec_info_type:
8700 done = vectorizable_shift (stmt, gsi, &vec_stmt, slp_node);
8701 gcc_assert (done);
8702 break;
8703
8704 case op_vec_info_type:
8705 done = vectorizable_operation (stmt, gsi, &vec_stmt, slp_node);
8706 gcc_assert (done);
8707 break;
8708
8709 case assignment_vec_info_type:
8710 done = vectorizable_assignment (stmt, gsi, &vec_stmt, slp_node);
8711 gcc_assert (done);
8712 break;
8713
8714 case load_vec_info_type:
8715 done = vectorizable_load (stmt, gsi, &vec_stmt, slp_node,
8716 slp_node_instance);
8717 gcc_assert (done);
8718 break;
8719
8720 case store_vec_info_type:
8721 done = vectorizable_store (stmt, gsi, &vec_stmt, slp_node);
8722 gcc_assert (done);
8723 if (STMT_VINFO_GROUPED_ACCESS (stmt_info) && !slp_node)
8724 {
8725 /* In case of interleaving, the whole chain is vectorized when the
8726 last store in the chain is reached. Store stmts before the last
8727 one are skipped, and there vec_stmt_info shouldn't be freed
8728 meanwhile. */
8729 *grouped_store = true;
8730 if (STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info))
8731 is_store = true;
8732 }
8733 else
8734 is_store = true;
8735 break;
8736
8737 case condition_vec_info_type:
8738 done = vectorizable_condition (stmt, gsi, &vec_stmt, NULL, 0, slp_node);
8739 gcc_assert (done);
8740 break;
8741
8742 case comparison_vec_info_type:
8743 done = vectorizable_comparison (stmt, gsi, &vec_stmt, NULL, slp_node);
8744 gcc_assert (done);
8745 break;
8746
8747 case call_vec_info_type:
8748 done = vectorizable_call (stmt, gsi, &vec_stmt, slp_node);
8749 stmt = gsi_stmt (*gsi);
8750 if (gimple_call_internal_p (stmt, IFN_MASK_STORE))
8751 is_store = true;
8752 break;
8753
8754 case call_simd_clone_vec_info_type:
8755 done = vectorizable_simd_clone_call (stmt, gsi, &vec_stmt, slp_node);
8756 stmt = gsi_stmt (*gsi);
8757 break;
8758
8759 case reduc_vec_info_type:
8760 done = vectorizable_reduction (stmt, gsi, &vec_stmt, slp_node);
8761 gcc_assert (done);
8762 break;
8763
8764 default:
8765 if (!STMT_VINFO_LIVE_P (stmt_info))
8766 {
8767 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8768 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
8769 "stmt not supported.\n");
8770 gcc_unreachable ();
8771 }
8772 }
8773
8774 /* Verify SLP vectorization doesn't mess with STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT.
8775 This would break hybrid SLP vectorization. */
8776 if (slp_node)
8777 gcc_assert (!vec_stmt
8778 && STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info) == old_vec_stmt);
8779
8780 /* Handle inner-loop stmts whose DEF is used in the loop-nest that
8781 is being vectorized, but outside the immediately enclosing loop. */
8782 if (vec_stmt
8783 && STMT_VINFO_LOOP_VINFO (stmt_info)
8784 && nested_in_vect_loop_p (LOOP_VINFO_LOOP (
8785 STMT_VINFO_LOOP_VINFO (stmt_info)), stmt)
8786 && STMT_VINFO_TYPE (stmt_info) != reduc_vec_info_type
8787 && (STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT (stmt_info) == vect_used_in_outer
8788 || STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT (stmt_info) ==
8789 vect_used_in_outer_by_reduction))
8790 {
8791 struct loop *innerloop = LOOP_VINFO_LOOP (
8792 STMT_VINFO_LOOP_VINFO (stmt_info))->inner;
8793 imm_use_iterator imm_iter;
8794 use_operand_p use_p;
8795 tree scalar_dest;
8796 gimple *exit_phi;
8797
8798 if (dump_enabled_p ())
8799 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
8800 "Record the vdef for outer-loop vectorization.\n");
8801
8802 /* Find the relevant loop-exit phi-node, and reord the vec_stmt there
8803 (to be used when vectorizing outer-loop stmts that use the DEF of
8804 STMT). */
8805 if (gimple_code (stmt) == GIMPLE_PHI)
8806 scalar_dest = PHI_RESULT (stmt);
8807 else
8808 scalar_dest = gimple_assign_lhs (stmt);
8809
8810 FOR_EACH_IMM_USE_FAST (use_p, imm_iter, scalar_dest)
8811 {
8812 if (!flow_bb_inside_loop_p (innerloop, gimple_bb (USE_STMT (use_p))))
8813 {
8814 exit_phi = USE_STMT (use_p);
8815 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (vinfo_for_stmt (exit_phi)) = vec_stmt;
8816 }
8817 }
8818 }
8819
8820 /* Handle stmts whose DEF is used outside the loop-nest that is
8821 being vectorized. */
8822 if (slp_node)
8823 {
8824 gimple *slp_stmt;
8825 int i;
8826 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (SLP_TREE_SCALAR_STMTS (slp_node), i, slp_stmt)
8827 {
8828 stmt_vec_info slp_stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (slp_stmt);
8829 if (STMT_VINFO_LIVE_P (slp_stmt_info)
8830 && STMT_VINFO_TYPE (slp_stmt_info) != reduc_vec_info_type)
8831 {
8832 done = vectorizable_live_operation (slp_stmt, gsi, slp_node, i,
8833 &vec_stmt);
8834 gcc_assert (done);
8835 }
8836 }
8837 }
8838 else if (STMT_VINFO_LIVE_P (stmt_info)
8839 && STMT_VINFO_TYPE (stmt_info) != reduc_vec_info_type)
8840 {
8841 done = vectorizable_live_operation (stmt, gsi, slp_node, -1, &vec_stmt);
8842 gcc_assert (done);
8843 }
8844
8845 if (vec_stmt)
8846 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (stmt_info) = vec_stmt;
8847
8848 return is_store;
8849}
8850
8851
8852/* Remove a group of stores (for SLP or interleaving), free their
8853 stmt_vec_info. */
8854
8855void
8856vect_remove_stores (gimple *first_stmt)
8857{
8858 gimple *next = first_stmt;
8859 gimple *tmp;
8860 gimple_stmt_iterator next_si;
8861
8862 while (next)
8863 {
8864 stmt_vec_info stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (next);
8865
8866 tmp = GROUP_NEXT_ELEMENT (stmt_info);
8867 if (is_pattern_stmt_p (stmt_info))
8868 next = STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (stmt_info);
8869 /* Free the attached stmt_vec_info and remove the stmt. */
8870 next_si = gsi_for_stmt (next);
8871 unlink_stmt_vdef (next);
8872 gsi_remove (&next_si, true);
8873 release_defs (next);
8874 free_stmt_vec_info (next);
8875 next = tmp;
8876 }
8877}
8878
8879
8880/* Function new_stmt_vec_info.
8881
8882 Create and initialize a new stmt_vec_info struct for STMT. */
8883
8884stmt_vec_info
8885new_stmt_vec_info (gimple *stmt, vec_info *vinfo)
8886{
8887 stmt_vec_info res;
8888 res = (stmt_vec_info) xcalloc (1, sizeof (struct _stmt_vec_info));
8889
8890 STMT_VINFO_TYPE (res) = undef_vec_info_type;
8891 STMT_VINFO_STMT (res) = stmt;
8892 res->vinfo = vinfo;
8893 STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT (res) = vect_unused_in_scope;
8894 STMT_VINFO_LIVE_P (res) = false;
8895 STMT_VINFO_VECTYPE (res) = NULL;
8896 STMT_VINFO_VEC_STMT (res) = NULL;
8897 STMT_VINFO_VECTORIZABLE (res) = true;
8898 STMT_VINFO_IN_PATTERN_P (res) = false;
8899 STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (res) = NULL;
8900 STMT_VINFO_PATTERN_DEF_SEQ (res) = NULL;
8901 STMT_VINFO_DATA_REF (res) = NULL;
8902 STMT_VINFO_VEC_REDUCTION_TYPE (res) = TREE_CODE_REDUCTION;
8903 STMT_VINFO_VEC_CONST_COND_REDUC_CODE (res) = ERROR_MARK;
8904
8905 STMT_VINFO_DR_BASE_ADDRESS (res) = NULL;
8906 STMT_VINFO_DR_OFFSET (res) = NULL;
8907 STMT_VINFO_DR_INIT (res) = NULL;
8908 STMT_VINFO_DR_STEP (res) = NULL;
8909 STMT_VINFO_DR_ALIGNED_TO (res) = NULL;
8910
8911 if (gimple_code (stmt) == GIMPLE_PHI
8912 && is_loop_header_bb_p (gimple_bb (stmt)))
8913 STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (res) = vect_unknown_def_type;
8914 else
8915 STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (res) = vect_internal_def;
8916
8917 STMT_VINFO_SAME_ALIGN_REFS (res).create (0);
8918 STMT_SLP_TYPE (res) = loop_vect;
8919 STMT_VINFO_NUM_SLP_USES (res) = 0;
8920
8921 GROUP_FIRST_ELEMENT (res) = NULL;
8922 GROUP_NEXT_ELEMENT (res) = NULL;
8923 GROUP_SIZE (res) = 0;
8924 GROUP_STORE_COUNT (res) = 0;
8925 GROUP_GAP (res) = 0;
8926 GROUP_SAME_DR_STMT (res) = NULL;
8927
8928 return res;
8929}
8930
8931
8932/* Create a hash table for stmt_vec_info. */
8933
8934void
8935init_stmt_vec_info_vec (void)
8936{
8937 gcc_assert (!stmt_vec_info_vec.exists ());
8938 stmt_vec_info_vec.create (50);
8939}
8940
8941
8942/* Free hash table for stmt_vec_info. */
8943
8944void
8945free_stmt_vec_info_vec (void)
8946{
8947 unsigned int i;
8948 stmt_vec_info info;
8949 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (stmt_vec_info_vec, i, info)
8950 if (info != NULL)
8951 free_stmt_vec_info (STMT_VINFO_STMT (info));
8952 gcc_assert (stmt_vec_info_vec.exists ());
8953 stmt_vec_info_vec.release ();
8954}
8955
8956
8957/* Free stmt vectorization related info. */
8958
8959void
8960free_stmt_vec_info (gimple *stmt)
8961{
8962 stmt_vec_info stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (stmt);
8963
8964 if (!stmt_info)
8965 return;
8966
8967 /* Check if this statement has a related "pattern stmt"
8968 (introduced by the vectorizer during the pattern recognition
8969 pass). Free pattern's stmt_vec_info and def stmt's stmt_vec_info
8970 too. */
8971 if (STMT_VINFO_IN_PATTERN_P (stmt_info))
8972 {
8973 stmt_vec_info patt_info
8974 = vinfo_for_stmt (STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (stmt_info));
8975 if (patt_info)
8976 {
8977 gimple_seq seq = STMT_VINFO_PATTERN_DEF_SEQ (patt_info);
8978 gimple *patt_stmt = STMT_VINFO_STMT (patt_info);
8979 gimple_set_bb (patt_stmt, NULL);
8980 tree lhs = gimple_get_lhs (patt_stmt);
8981 if (lhs && TREE_CODE (lhs) == SSA_NAME)
8982 release_ssa_name (lhs);
8983 if (seq)
8984 {
8985 gimple_stmt_iterator si;
8986 for (si = gsi_start (seq); !gsi_end_p (si); gsi_next (&si))
8987 {
8988 gimple *seq_stmt = gsi_stmt (si);
8989 gimple_set_bb (seq_stmt, NULL);
8990 lhs = gimple_get_lhs (seq_stmt);
8991 if (lhs && TREE_CODE (lhs) == SSA_NAME)
8992 release_ssa_name (lhs);
8993 free_stmt_vec_info (seq_stmt);
8994 }
8995 }
8996 free_stmt_vec_info (patt_stmt);
8997 }
8998 }
8999
9000 STMT_VINFO_SAME_ALIGN_REFS (stmt_info).release ();
9001 STMT_VINFO_SIMD_CLONE_INFO (stmt_info).release ();
9002 set_vinfo_for_stmt (stmt, NULL);
9003 free (stmt_info);
9004}
9005
9006
9007/* Function get_vectype_for_scalar_type_and_size.
9008
9009 Returns the vector type corresponding to SCALAR_TYPE and SIZE as supported
9010 by the target. */
9011
9012static tree
9013get_vectype_for_scalar_type_and_size (tree scalar_type, unsigned size)
9014{
9015 tree orig_scalar_type = scalar_type;
9016 machine_mode inner_mode = TYPE_MODE (scalar_type);
9017 machine_mode simd_mode;
9018 unsigned int nbytes = GET_MODE_SIZE (inner_mode);
9019 int nunits;
9020 tree vectype;
9021
9022 if (nbytes == 0)
9023 return NULL_TREE;
9024
9025 if (GET_MODE_CLASS (inner_mode) != MODE_INT
9026 && GET_MODE_CLASS (inner_mode) != MODE_FLOAT)
9027 return NULL_TREE;
9028
9029 /* For vector types of elements whose mode precision doesn't
9030 match their types precision we use a element type of mode
9031 precision. The vectorization routines will have to make sure
9032 they support the proper result truncation/extension.
9033 We also make sure to build vector types with INTEGER_TYPE
9034 component type only. */
9035 if (INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (scalar_type)
9036 && (GET_MODE_BITSIZE (inner_mode) != TYPE_PRECISION (scalar_type)
9037 || TREE_CODE (scalar_type) != INTEGER_TYPE))
9038 scalar_type = build_nonstandard_integer_type (GET_MODE_BITSIZE (inner_mode),
9039 TYPE_UNSIGNED (scalar_type));
9040
9041 /* We shouldn't end up building VECTOR_TYPEs of non-scalar components.
9042 When the component mode passes the above test simply use a type
9043 corresponding to that mode. The theory is that any use that
9044 would cause problems with this will disable vectorization anyway. */
9045 else if (!SCALAR_FLOAT_TYPE_P (scalar_type)
9046 && !INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (scalar_type))
9047 scalar_type = lang_hooks.types.type_for_mode (inner_mode, 1);
9048
9049 /* We can't build a vector type of elements with alignment bigger than
9050 their size. */
9051 else if (nbytes < TYPE_ALIGN_UNIT (scalar_type))
9052 scalar_type = lang_hooks.types.type_for_mode (inner_mode,
9053 TYPE_UNSIGNED (scalar_type));
9054
9055 /* If we felt back to using the mode fail if there was
9056 no scalar type for it. */
9057 if (scalar_type == NULL_TREE)
9058 return NULL_TREE;
9059
9060 /* If no size was supplied use the mode the target prefers. Otherwise
9061 lookup a vector mode of the specified size. */
9062 if (size == 0)
9063 simd_mode = targetm.vectorize.preferred_simd_mode (inner_mode);
9064 else
9065 simd_mode = mode_for_vector (inner_mode, size / nbytes);
9066 nunits = GET_MODE_SIZE (simd_mode) / nbytes;
9067 if (nunits <= 1)
9068 return NULL_TREE;
9069
9070 vectype = build_vector_type (scalar_type, nunits);
9071
9072 if (!VECTOR_MODE_P (TYPE_MODE (vectype))
9073 && !INTEGRAL_MODE_P (TYPE_MODE (vectype)))
9074 return NULL_TREE;
9075
9076 /* Re-attach the address-space qualifier if we canonicalized the scalar
9077 type. */
9078 if (TYPE_ADDR_SPACE (orig_scalar_type) != TYPE_ADDR_SPACE (vectype))
9079 return build_qualified_type
9080 (vectype, KEEP_QUAL_ADDR_SPACE (TYPE_QUALS (orig_scalar_type)));
9081
9082 return vectype;
9083}
9084
9085unsigned int current_vector_size;
9086
9087/* Function get_vectype_for_scalar_type.
9088
9089 Returns the vector type corresponding to SCALAR_TYPE as supported
9090 by the target. */
9091
9092tree
9093get_vectype_for_scalar_type (tree scalar_type)
9094{
9095 tree vectype;
9096 vectype = get_vectype_for_scalar_type_and_size (scalar_type,
9097 current_vector_size);
9098 if (vectype
9099 && current_vector_size == 0)
9100 current_vector_size = GET_MODE_SIZE (TYPE_MODE (vectype));
9101 return vectype;
9102}
9103
9104/* Function get_mask_type_for_scalar_type.
9105
9106 Returns the mask type corresponding to a result of comparison
9107 of vectors of specified SCALAR_TYPE as supported by target. */
9108
9109tree
9110get_mask_type_for_scalar_type (tree scalar_type)
9111{
9112 tree vectype = get_vectype_for_scalar_type (scalar_type);
9113
9114 if (!vectype)
9115 return NULL;
9116
9117 return build_truth_vector_type (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype),
9118 current_vector_size);
9119}
9120
9121/* Function get_same_sized_vectype
9122
9123 Returns a vector type corresponding to SCALAR_TYPE of size
9124 VECTOR_TYPE if supported by the target. */
9125
9126tree
9127get_same_sized_vectype (tree scalar_type, tree vector_type)
9128{
9129 if (VECT_SCALAR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (scalar_type))
9130 return build_same_sized_truth_vector_type (vector_type);
9131
9132 return get_vectype_for_scalar_type_and_size
9133 (scalar_type, GET_MODE_SIZE (TYPE_MODE (vector_type)));
9134}
9135
9136/* Function vect_is_simple_use.
9137
9138 Input:
9139 VINFO - the vect info of the loop or basic block that is being vectorized.
9140 OPERAND - operand in the loop or bb.
9141 Output:
9142 DEF_STMT - the defining stmt in case OPERAND is an SSA_NAME.
9143 DT - the type of definition
9144
9145 Returns whether a stmt with OPERAND can be vectorized.
9146 For loops, supportable operands are constants, loop invariants, and operands
9147 that are defined by the current iteration of the loop. Unsupportable
9148 operands are those that are defined by a previous iteration of the loop (as
9149 is the case in reduction/induction computations).
9150 For basic blocks, supportable operands are constants and bb invariants.
9151 For now, operands defined outside the basic block are not supported. */
9152
9153bool
9154vect_is_simple_use (tree operand, vec_info *vinfo,
9155 gimple **def_stmt, enum vect_def_type *dt)
9156{
9157 *def_stmt = NULL;
9158 *dt = vect_unknown_def_type;
9159
9160 if (dump_enabled_p ())
9161 {
9162 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location,
9163 "vect_is_simple_use: operand ");
9164 dump_generic_expr (MSG_NOTE, TDF_SLIM, operand);
9165 dump_printf (MSG_NOTE, "\n");
9166 }
9167
9168 if (CONSTANT_CLASS_P (operand))
9169 {
9170 *dt = vect_constant_def;
9171 return true;
9172 }
9173
9174 if (is_gimple_min_invariant (operand))
9175 {
9176 *dt = vect_external_def;
9177 return true;
9178 }
9179
9180 if (TREE_CODE (operand) != SSA_NAME)
9181 {
9182 if (dump_enabled_p ())
9183 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
9184 "not ssa-name.\n");
9185 return false;
9186 }
9187
9188 if (SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (operand))
9189 {
9190 *dt = vect_external_def;
9191 return true;
9192 }
9193
9194 *def_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (operand);
9195 if (dump_enabled_p ())
9196 {
9197 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location, "def_stmt: ");
9198 dump_gimple_stmt (MSG_NOTE, TDF_SLIM, *def_stmt, 0);
9199 }
9200
9201 if (! vect_stmt_in_region_p (vinfo, *def_stmt))
9202 *dt = vect_external_def;
9203 else
9204 {
9205 stmt_vec_info stmt_vinfo = vinfo_for_stmt (*def_stmt);
9206 *dt = STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (stmt_vinfo);
9207 }
9208
9209 if (dump_enabled_p ())
9210 {
9211 dump_printf_loc (MSG_NOTE, vect_location, "type of def: ");
9212 switch (*dt)
9213 {
9214 case vect_uninitialized_def:
9215 dump_printf (MSG_NOTE, "uninitialized\n");
9216 break;
9217 case vect_constant_def:
9218 dump_printf (MSG_NOTE, "constant\n");
9219 break;
9220 case vect_external_def:
9221 dump_printf (MSG_NOTE, "external\n");
9222 break;
9223 case vect_internal_def:
9224 dump_printf (MSG_NOTE, "internal\n");
9225 break;
9226 case vect_induction_def:
9227 dump_printf (MSG_NOTE, "induction\n");
9228 break;
9229 case vect_reduction_def:
9230 dump_printf (MSG_NOTE, "reduction\n");
9231 break;
9232 case vect_double_reduction_def:
9233 dump_printf (MSG_NOTE, "double reduction\n");
9234 break;
9235 case vect_nested_cycle:
9236 dump_printf (MSG_NOTE, "nested cycle\n");
9237 break;
9238 case vect_unknown_def_type:
9239 dump_printf (MSG_NOTE, "unknown\n");
9240 break;
9241 }
9242 }
9243
9244 if (*dt == vect_unknown_def_type)
9245 {
9246 if (dump_enabled_p ())
9247 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
9248 "Unsupported pattern.\n");
9249 return false;
9250 }
9251
9252 switch (gimple_code (*def_stmt))
9253 {
9254 case GIMPLE_PHI:
9255 case GIMPLE_ASSIGN:
9256 case GIMPLE_CALL:
9257 break;
9258 default:
9259 if (dump_enabled_p ())
9260 dump_printf_loc (MSG_MISSED_OPTIMIZATION, vect_location,
9261 "unsupported defining stmt:\n");
9262 return false;
9263 }
9264
9265 return true;
9266}
9267
9268/* Function vect_is_simple_use.
9269
9270 Same as vect_is_simple_use but also determines the vector operand
9271 type of OPERAND and stores it to *VECTYPE. If the definition of
9272 OPERAND is vect_uninitialized_def, vect_constant_def or
9273 vect_external_def *VECTYPE will be set to NULL_TREE and the caller
9274 is responsible to compute the best suited vector type for the
9275 scalar operand. */
9276
9277bool
9278vect_is_simple_use (tree operand, vec_info *vinfo,
9279 gimple **def_stmt, enum vect_def_type *dt, tree *vectype)
9280{
9281 if (!vect_is_simple_use (operand, vinfo, def_stmt, dt))
9282 return false;
9283
9284 /* Now get a vector type if the def is internal, otherwise supply
9285 NULL_TREE and leave it up to the caller to figure out a proper
9286 type for the use stmt. */
9287 if (*dt == vect_internal_def
9288 || *dt == vect_induction_def
9289 || *dt == vect_reduction_def
9290 || *dt == vect_double_reduction_def
9291 || *dt == vect_nested_cycle)
9292 {
9293 stmt_vec_info stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (*def_stmt);
9294
9295 if (STMT_VINFO_IN_PATTERN_P (stmt_info)
9296 && !STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT (stmt_info)
9297 && !STMT_VINFO_LIVE_P (stmt_info))
9298 stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (STMT_VINFO_RELATED_STMT (stmt_info));
9299
9300 *vectype = STMT_VINFO_VECTYPE (stmt_info);
9301 gcc_assert (*vectype != NULL_TREE);
9302 }
9303 else if (*dt == vect_uninitialized_def
9304 || *dt == vect_constant_def
9305 || *dt == vect_external_def)
9306 *vectype = NULL_TREE;
9307 else
9308 gcc_unreachable ();
9309
9310 return true;
9311}
9312
9313
9314/* Function supportable_widening_operation
9315
9316 Check whether an operation represented by the code CODE is a
9317 widening operation that is supported by the target platform in
9318 vector form (i.e., when operating on arguments of type VECTYPE_IN
9319 producing a result of type VECTYPE_OUT).
9320
9321 Widening operations we currently support are NOP (CONVERT), FLOAT
9322 and WIDEN_MULT. This function checks if these operations are supported
9323 by the target platform either directly (via vector tree-codes), or via
9324 target builtins.
9325
9326 Output:
9327 - CODE1 and CODE2 are codes of vector operations to be used when
9328 vectorizing the operation, if available.
9329 - MULTI_STEP_CVT determines the number of required intermediate steps in
9330 case of multi-step conversion (like char->short->int - in that case
9331 MULTI_STEP_CVT will be 1).
9332 - INTERM_TYPES contains the intermediate type required to perform the
9333 widening operation (short in the above example). */
9334
9335bool
9336supportable_widening_operation (enum tree_code code, gimple *stmt,
9337 tree vectype_out, tree vectype_in,
9338 enum tree_code *code1, enum tree_code *code2,
9339 int *multi_step_cvt,
9340 vec<tree> *interm_types)
9341{
9342 stmt_vec_info stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (stmt);
9343 loop_vec_info loop_info = STMT_VINFO_LOOP_VINFO (stmt_info);
9344 struct loop *vect_loop = NULL;
9345 machine_mode vec_mode;
9346 enum insn_code icode1, icode2;
9347 optab optab1, optab2;
9348 tree vectype = vectype_in;
9349 tree wide_vectype = vectype_out;
9350 enum tree_code c1, c2;
9351 int i;
9352 tree prev_type, intermediate_type;
9353 machine_mode intermediate_mode, prev_mode;
9354 optab optab3, optab4;
9355
9356 *multi_step_cvt = 0;
9357 if (loop_info)
9358 vect_loop = LOOP_VINFO_LOOP (loop_info);
9359
9360 switch (code)
9361 {
9362 case WIDEN_MULT_EXPR:
9363 /* The result of a vectorized widening operation usually requires
9364 two vectors (because the widened results do not fit into one vector).
9365 The generated vector results would normally be expected to be
9366 generated in the same order as in the original scalar computation,
9367 i.e. if 8 results are generated in each vector iteration, they are
9368 to be organized as follows:
9369 vect1: [res1,res2,res3,res4],
9370 vect2: [res5,res6,res7,res8].
9371
9372 However, in the special case that the result of the widening
9373 operation is used in a reduction computation only, the order doesn't
9374 matter (because when vectorizing a reduction we change the order of
9375 the computation). Some targets can take advantage of this and
9376 generate more efficient code. For example, targets like Altivec,
9377 that support widen_mult using a sequence of {mult_even,mult_odd}
9378 generate the following vectors:
9379 vect1: [res1,res3,res5,res7],
9380 vect2: [res2,res4,res6,res8].
9381
9382 When vectorizing outer-loops, we execute the inner-loop sequentially
9383 (each vectorized inner-loop iteration contributes to VF outer-loop
9384 iterations in parallel). We therefore don't allow to change the
9385 order of the computation in the inner-loop during outer-loop
9386 vectorization. */
9387 /* TODO: Another case in which order doesn't *really* matter is when we
9388 widen and then contract again, e.g. (short)((int)x * y >> 8).
9389 Normally, pack_trunc performs an even/odd permute, whereas the
9390 repack from an even/odd expansion would be an interleave, which
9391 would be significantly simpler for e.g. AVX2. */
9392 /* In any case, in order to avoid duplicating the code below, recurse
9393 on VEC_WIDEN_MULT_EVEN_EXPR. If it succeeds, all the return values
9394 are properly set up for the caller. If we fail, we'll continue with
9395 a VEC_WIDEN_MULT_LO/HI_EXPR check. */
9396 if (vect_loop
9397 && STMT_VINFO_RELEVANT (stmt_info) == vect_used_by_reduction
9398 && !nested_in_vect_loop_p (vect_loop, stmt)
9399 && supportable_widening_operation (VEC_WIDEN_MULT_EVEN_EXPR,
9400 stmt, vectype_out, vectype_in,
9401 code1, code2, multi_step_cvt,
9402 interm_types))
9403 {
9404 /* Elements in a vector with vect_used_by_reduction property cannot
9405 be reordered if the use chain with this property does not have the
9406 same operation. One such an example is s += a * b, where elements
9407 in a and b cannot be reordered. Here we check if the vector defined
9408 by STMT is only directly used in the reduction statement. */
9409 tree lhs = gimple_assign_lhs (stmt);
9410 use_operand_p dummy;
9411 gimple *use_stmt;
9412 stmt_vec_info use_stmt_info = NULL;
9413 if (single_imm_use (lhs, &dummy, &use_stmt)
9414 && (use_stmt_info = vinfo_for_stmt (use_stmt))
9415 && STMT_VINFO_DEF_TYPE (use_stmt_info) == vect_reduction_def)
9416 return true;
9417 }
9418 c1 = VEC_WIDEN_MULT_LO_EXPR;
9419 c2 = VEC_WIDEN_MULT_HI_EXPR;
9420 break;
9421
9422 case DOT_PROD_EXPR:
9423 c1 = DOT_PROD_EXPR;
9424 c2 = DOT_PROD_EXPR;
9425 break;
9426
9427 case SAD_EXPR:
9428 c1 = SAD_EXPR;
9429 c2 = SAD_EXPR;
9430 break;
9431
9432 case VEC_WIDEN_MULT_EVEN_EXPR:
9433 /* Support the recursion induced just above. */
9434 c1 = VEC_WIDEN_MULT_EVEN_EXPR;
9435 c2 = VEC_WIDEN_MULT_ODD_EXPR;
9436 break;
9437
9438 case WIDEN_LSHIFT_EXPR:
9439 c1 = VEC_WIDEN_LSHIFT_LO_EXPR;
9440 c2 = VEC_WIDEN_LSHIFT_HI_EXPR;
9441 break;
9442
9443 CASE_CONVERT:
9444 c1 = VEC_UNPACK_LO_EXPR;
9445 c2 = VEC_UNPACK_HI_EXPR;
9446 break;
9447
9448 case FLOAT_EXPR:
9449 c1 = VEC_UNPACK_FLOAT_LO_EXPR;
9450 c2 = VEC_UNPACK_FLOAT_HI_EXPR;
9451 break;
9452
9453 case FIX_TRUNC_EXPR:
9454 /* ??? Not yet implemented due to missing VEC_UNPACK_FIX_TRUNC_HI_EXPR/
9455 VEC_UNPACK_FIX_TRUNC_LO_EXPR tree codes and optabs used for
9456 computing the operation. */
9457 return false;
9458
9459 default:
9460 gcc_unreachable ();
9461 }
9462
9463 if (BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN && c1 != VEC_WIDEN_MULT_EVEN_EXPR)
9464 std::swap (c1, c2);
9465
9466 if (code == FIX_TRUNC_EXPR)
9467 {
9468 /* The signedness is determined from output operand. */
9469 optab1 = optab_for_tree_code (c1, vectype_out, optab_default);
9470 optab2 = optab_for_tree_code (c2, vectype_out, optab_default);
9471 }
9472 else
9473 {
9474 optab1 = optab_for_tree_code (c1, vectype, optab_default);
9475 optab2 = optab_for_tree_code (c2, vectype, optab_default);
9476 }
9477
9478 if (!optab1 || !optab2)
9479 return false;
9480
9481 vec_mode = TYPE_MODE (vectype);
9482 if ((icode1 = optab_handler (optab1, vec_mode)) == CODE_FOR_nothing
9483 || (icode2 = optab_handler (optab2, vec_mode)) == CODE_FOR_nothing)
9484 return false;
9485
9486 *code1 = c1;
9487 *code2 = c2;
9488
9489 if (insn_data[icode1].operand[0].mode == TYPE_MODE (wide_vectype)
9490 && insn_data[icode2].operand[0].mode == TYPE_MODE (wide_vectype))
9491 /* For scalar masks we may have different boolean
9492 vector types having the same QImode. Thus we
9493 add additional check for elements number. */
9494 return (!VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (vectype)
9495 || (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype) / 2
9496 == TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (wide_vectype)));
9497
9498 /* Check if it's a multi-step conversion that can be done using intermediate
9499 types. */
9500
9501 prev_type = vectype;
9502 prev_mode = vec_mode;
9503
9504 if (!CONVERT_EXPR_CODE_P (code))
9505 return false;
9506
9507 /* We assume here that there will not be more than MAX_INTERM_CVT_STEPS
9508 intermediate steps in promotion sequence. We try
9509 MAX_INTERM_CVT_STEPS to get to NARROW_VECTYPE, and fail if we do
9510 not. */
9511 interm_types->create (MAX_INTERM_CVT_STEPS);
9512 for (i = 0; i < MAX_INTERM_CVT_STEPS; i++)
9513 {
9514 intermediate_mode = insn_data[icode1].operand[0].mode;
9515 if (VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (prev_type))
9516 {
9517 intermediate_type
9518 = build_truth_vector_type (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (prev_type) / 2,
9519 current_vector_size);
9520 if (intermediate_mode != TYPE_MODE (intermediate_type))
9521 return false;
9522 }
9523 else
9524 intermediate_type
9525 = lang_hooks.types.type_for_mode (intermediate_mode,
9526 TYPE_UNSIGNED (prev_type));
9527
9528 optab3 = optab_for_tree_code (c1, intermediate_type, optab_default);
9529 optab4 = optab_for_tree_code (c2, intermediate_type, optab_default);
9530
9531 if (!optab3 || !optab4
9532 || (icode1 = optab_handler (optab1, prev_mode)) == CODE_FOR_nothing
9533 || insn_data[icode1].operand[0].mode != intermediate_mode
9534 || (icode2 = optab_handler (optab2, prev_mode)) == CODE_FOR_nothing
9535 || insn_data[icode2].operand[0].mode != intermediate_mode
9536 || ((icode1 = optab_handler (optab3, intermediate_mode))
9537 == CODE_FOR_nothing)
9538 || ((icode2 = optab_handler (optab4, intermediate_mode))
9539 == CODE_FOR_nothing))
9540 break;
9541
9542 interm_types->quick_push (intermediate_type);
9543 (*multi_step_cvt)++;
9544
9545 if (insn_data[icode1].operand[0].mode == TYPE_MODE (wide_vectype)
9546 && insn_data[icode2].operand[0].mode == TYPE_MODE (wide_vectype))
9547 return (!VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (vectype)
9548 || (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (intermediate_type) / 2
9549 == TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (wide_vectype)));
9550
9551 prev_type = intermediate_type;
9552 prev_mode = intermediate_mode;
9553 }
9554
9555 interm_types->release ();
9556 return false;
9557}
9558
9559
9560/* Function supportable_narrowing_operation
9561
9562 Check whether an operation represented by the code CODE is a
9563 narrowing operation that is supported by the target platform in
9564 vector form (i.e., when operating on arguments of type VECTYPE_IN
9565 and producing a result of type VECTYPE_OUT).
9566
9567 Narrowing operations we currently support are NOP (CONVERT) and
9568 FIX_TRUNC. This function checks if these operations are supported by
9569 the target platform directly via vector tree-codes.
9570
9571 Output:
9572 - CODE1 is the code of a vector operation to be used when
9573 vectorizing the operation, if available.
9574 - MULTI_STEP_CVT determines the number of required intermediate steps in
9575 case of multi-step conversion (like int->short->char - in that case
9576 MULTI_STEP_CVT will be 1).
9577 - INTERM_TYPES contains the intermediate type required to perform the
9578 narrowing operation (short in the above example). */
9579
9580bool
9581supportable_narrowing_operation (enum tree_code code,
9582 tree vectype_out, tree vectype_in,
9583 enum tree_code *code1, int *multi_step_cvt,
9584 vec<tree> *interm_types)
9585{
9586 machine_mode vec_mode;
9587 enum insn_code icode1;
9588 optab optab1, interm_optab;
9589 tree vectype = vectype_in;
9590 tree narrow_vectype = vectype_out;
9591 enum tree_code c1;
9592 tree intermediate_type, prev_type;
9593 machine_mode intermediate_mode, prev_mode;
9594 int i;
9595 bool uns;
9596
9597 *multi_step_cvt = 0;
9598 switch (code)
9599 {
9600 CASE_CONVERT:
9601 c1 = VEC_PACK_TRUNC_EXPR;
9602 break;
9603
9604 case FIX_TRUNC_EXPR:
9605 c1 = VEC_PACK_FIX_TRUNC_EXPR;
9606 break;
9607
9608 case FLOAT_EXPR:
9609 /* ??? Not yet implemented due to missing VEC_PACK_FLOAT_EXPR
9610 tree code and optabs used for computing the operation. */
9611 return false;
9612
9613 default:
9614 gcc_unreachable ();
9615 }
9616
9617 if (code == FIX_TRUNC_EXPR)
9618 /* The signedness is determined from output operand. */
9619 optab1 = optab_for_tree_code (c1, vectype_out, optab_default);
9620 else
9621 optab1 = optab_for_tree_code (c1, vectype, optab_default);
9622
9623 if (!optab1)
9624 return false;
9625
9626 vec_mode = TYPE_MODE (vectype);
9627 if ((icode1 = optab_handler (optab1, vec_mode)) == CODE_FOR_nothing)
9628 return false;
9629
9630 *code1 = c1;
9631
9632 if (insn_data[icode1].operand[0].mode == TYPE_MODE (narrow_vectype))
9633 /* For scalar masks we may have different boolean
9634 vector types having the same QImode. Thus we
9635 add additional check for elements number. */
9636 return (!VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (vectype)
9637 || (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (vectype) * 2
9638 == TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (narrow_vectype)));
9639
9640 /* Check if it's a multi-step conversion that can be done using intermediate
9641 types. */
9642 prev_mode = vec_mode;
9643 prev_type = vectype;
9644 if (code == FIX_TRUNC_EXPR)
9645 uns = TYPE_UNSIGNED (vectype_out);
9646 else
9647 uns = TYPE_UNSIGNED (vectype);
9648
9649 /* For multi-step FIX_TRUNC_EXPR prefer signed floating to integer
9650 conversion over unsigned, as unsigned FIX_TRUNC_EXPR is often more
9651 costly than signed. */
9652 if (code == FIX_TRUNC_EXPR && uns)
9653 {
9654 enum insn_code icode2;
9655
9656 intermediate_type
9657 = lang_hooks.types.type_for_mode (TYPE_MODE (vectype_out), 0);
9658 interm_optab
9659 = optab_for_tree_code (c1, intermediate_type, optab_default);
9660 if (interm_optab != unknown_optab
9661 && (icode2 = optab_handler (optab1, vec_mode)) != CODE_FOR_nothing
9662 && insn_data[icode1].operand[0].mode
9663 == insn_data[icode2].operand[0].mode)
9664 {
9665 uns = false;
9666 optab1 = interm_optab;
9667 icode1 = icode2;
9668 }
9669 }
9670
9671 /* We assume here that there will not be more than MAX_INTERM_CVT_STEPS
9672 intermediate steps in promotion sequence. We try
9673 MAX_INTERM_CVT_STEPS to get to NARROW_VECTYPE, and fail if we do not. */
9674 interm_types->create (MAX_INTERM_CVT_STEPS);
9675 for (i = 0; i < MAX_INTERM_CVT_STEPS; i++)
9676 {
9677 intermediate_mode = insn_data[icode1].operand[0].mode;
9678 if (VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (prev_type))
9679 {
9680 intermediate_type
9681 = build_truth_vector_type (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (prev_type) * 2,
9682 current_vector_size);
9683 if (intermediate_mode != TYPE_MODE (intermediate_type))
9684 return false;
9685 }
9686 else
9687 intermediate_type
9688 = lang_hooks.types.type_for_mode (intermediate_mode, uns);
9689 interm_optab
9690 = optab_for_tree_code (VEC_PACK_TRUNC_EXPR, intermediate_type,
9691 optab_default);
9692 if (!interm_optab
9693 || ((icode1 = optab_handler (optab1, prev_mode)) == CODE_FOR_nothing)
9694 || insn_data[icode1].operand[0].mode != intermediate_mode
9695 || ((icode1 = optab_handler (interm_optab, intermediate_mode))
9696 == CODE_FOR_nothing))
9697 break;
9698
9699 interm_types->quick_push (intermediate_type);
9700 (*multi_step_cvt)++;
9701
9702 if (insn_data[icode1].operand[0].mode == TYPE_MODE (narrow_vectype))
9703 return (!VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (vectype)
9704 || (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (intermediate_type) * 2
9705 == TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (narrow_vectype)));
9706
9707 prev_mode = intermediate_mode;
9708 prev_type = intermediate_type;
9709 optab1 = interm_optab;
9710 }
9711
9712 interm_types->release ();
9713 return false;
9714}
